title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Should be thick enough to push from spoon into deep, hot cooking oil.
If not, add a small amount of corn meal mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into deep, very hot cooking oil, being careful not to splatter.
Cook until hush puppies are brown all over.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add egg and pumpkin.
Sift in all other dry ingredients.
Add water and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Makes 3 loaves.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix and bake according to package in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Poke holes in warm brownies with a fork about 1 inch apart.
Brush with butter, Cool Whip and candy crumbs.
Prepare chocolate mousse according to package, omitting chilling.
Place 1/2 crumbled brownies in bottom of 3 quart trifle bowl.
Top with mousse, cherry pie filling and whipped cream.
Repeat layers, ending with whipped cream on top.
Garnish with chocolate curlies. Chill 8 hours.
Serves 16 to 18.

title: king's ranch chicken
directions: Tear tortillas into large pieces and line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with them.
In a separate bowl mix the mushroom soup, chicken soup, tomatoes, broth and chili powder.
Put a layer of chicken over the tortillas, then onions, cheese and soup mixture.
Do this until you use all ingredients.
Top with cheese. Cook 1 hour at 300°.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and put in 9x13 pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Let Cool.

title: easy peanut butter candy
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and Marshmallow Creme together.
Melt Parkay margarine and pour over mixed ingredients and mix together.
Spread onto a cookie sheet and cool, then cut into squares.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites very stiff.
Add sugar and baking powder. Fold in cracker crumbs and pecans.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased pie pan for 35 minutes at 300°.
Cool and top with whipping cream.

title: broccoli strata casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Toast 4 slices of bread and place in ungreased 9 x 12-inch Pyrex pan.
Top with American cheese.
Add drained broccoli.
Place Swiss cheese on top of broccoli. Beat eggs. Blend in milk, onion, salt, mustard and dash of pepper. Pour over casserole. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Make bread crumb topping.
Melt some butter and add bread crumbs.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: quick cabbage lasagne
directions: Take the core from the cabbage.
Parboil the cabbage leaves. Brown the meat, onion and green pepper (amount according to preference).
Add the cooked rice and sauce.
Use a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Begin with a small amount of sauce on the bottom of the dish, then make layers as follows:
half of the meat and rice mixture, then the cabbage leaves (folded and laid across the meat layer), cheese on top of the sauce, then meat mixture, cabbage leaves, sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese log
directions: Cream the cream cheese at room temperature.
Grate dried beef. Add half to cream cheese, onions and Accent.
Chill in refrigerator.
Shape into 2 or 4 logs.
Roll into the other half of dried beef.
Store in refrigerator wrapped in wax paper until ready to serve.

title: country corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in greased 9 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; salt and pepper to taste.
Drain off excess fat.
Add cream of chicken soup and 2/3 can of water.
Combine with celery, onion and green pepper and place in baking dish or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with bag of frozen Tater Tots.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: mammaw's chocolate icing
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan slowly.
Combine cocoa, salt and sugar and add to melted butter along with milk.
Boil 3 minutes. Add vanilla and cool.
Beat until smooth.
Very good.

title: anytime soup(especially good for diets.)
directions: Put the first 9 ingredients in a large pan. Add the last 3. Simmer until vegetables are tender.
(Can be frozen in small amounts.
Great for lunch.)

title: "grouper key largo"
directions: Two large frying pans are needed.
In one, saute the shrimp, scallops and mushrooms in 1/2 of bacon drippings.
When they are just about done (5 minutes), add crab and bread crumbs.
Turn off heat and hold this mixture.

title: creamy cabbage
directions: In 2-quart casserole, place cabbage, onions and water.
Cover with lid or Saran.
Microwave on High 4 minutes; stir.
Cut cream cheese in small chunks and add to cabbage along with celery seed, salt and butter.
Toss lightly until cheese and butter are melted.

title: butter pecan cookies(for my sister, kimmy, with love)
directions: Cream butter and sugars until light.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: humdingers
directions: Combine butter, dates, nuts and sugar in medium saucepan; heat to simmer. Let simmer 8 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and Rice Krispies. Blend. Let cool briefly. While still warm, roll into balls and roll in confectioners sugar. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: cream of corn soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot over medium heat.
Add onions and celery; cook 10 minutes, stir often.
Add milk, corn, salt and pepper.
Cook 30 minutes, stir often.

title: bisquick banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in one bow and beat for one minute.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pan, which has been greased or sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 55-60 minutes, or longer.
Take a toothpick test to see if the bread is done.
Note: Reduced Fat Bisquick may be used in this recipe.

title: swiss chicken and rice
directions: Coat chicken pieces in mixture of first 4 ingredients.
Brown coated chicken pieces in butter (20 minutes).
Place in casserole dish.
Combine rest of ingredients in saucepan; cook for 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour mixture over chicken pieces.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: ziti casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix in large bowl the noodles, 1 1/2 cups sauce, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, parsley, egg, oregano and pepper.
Put 1/2 cup sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread mixture into pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: blueberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello	in
boiling water.
Add blueberries and juice and pineapple
with
its juice.
Pour into 9-inch square pan. Refrigerate until
set.
Make topping by mixing together cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on jello. Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Cut into squares.

title: festive fruit casserole
directions: Reserve juices from fruit.
Butter baking dish well.
Layer the crumbled cookies, some fruit, more cookie crumbs and some melted butter.
Repeat layers.
Lastly, mix bourbon or rum with reserved juices and brown sugar.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zats black beans and chicken
directions: Mix together chicken, chopped bacon, cheese, garlic powder, oregano, hot sauce, salt and pepper.
Prepare black beans and rice according to package directions.
Reduce cook time by 10 minutes. Stir chicken mixture into rice and let stand 10 minutes.
Turn into casserole dish and serve hot with sour cream and green onions as garnish.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add buttermilk and stir.
Blend in dates, pecans, eggs and pumpkin.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: baked apples
directions: Using 1 or 2 apples per person, wash, core and peel about 1/3 down from top.
Place apples in baking dish.
Fill apple with butter, sugar and any other filling you'd like. Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover, basting 2 or 3 times and bake 15 minutes longer or until tender.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix lightly and drop with spoon on greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken, okra and sausage gumbo
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large Dutch oven.
Simmer, covered, 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Skim fat from broth.
When cool enough to handle, remove bones and skin from chicken and discard.
Cut meat in pieces.
Leave broth in pot.
Brown sausage in microwave or small skillet.
Drain on paper towels.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Add tomatoes, onion and sausage to broth in pot.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Add okra, corn, red pepper seasoning and chicken. Simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until okra is tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over rice.

title: aunt grace's chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soda and vanilla.
Cook on low heat until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add soda and vanilla and stir.
Be careful not to let mixture boil over when soda is added.
Remove from stove and cool slightly.
Spread on warm cake layers.

title: cabbage rolls with venison
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter.
Mix with rice and seasoning. Blanch leaves in boiling water.
Place meat mixture in center of leaves.
Fold over and secure with toothpick.
Place in greased dish and cover with tomato juice.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan cookies or pecanettes
directions: Mix ingredients together well and drop by teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove cookies immediately from sheet.
Makes 35 cookies.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Clean the insides out of the tomato.
Set aside.
Mix tuna, Miracle Whip and celery or onion together.
Spoon into tomato. Sprinkle paprika onto the top.
Serves 6.

title: easy one-dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, the ham and onion powder in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix baking mix and milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Let stand at least 5 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Good for breakfast, brunch or Sunday night supper.

title: aunt chris' chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken pieces first in flour, then egg, then bread crumbs.
Put oil in bottom of baking pan.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes; turn and bake an additional 25 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 3 minutes. Pour into 3 cake pans or one 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done. Let sit and cool.

title: baked fillet of fish
directions: Combine seasonings and sprinkle on both sides of fish. Make a sauce with the melted butter, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Baste fish with sauce mixture. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes. Halfway through, turn over and baste again with sauce mixture.

title: new potato salad
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, mustard, dill weed, salt and pepper. Mix potatoes and onion; add sauce gently to coat.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: bad hombre chili
directions: Brown beef with garlic and onions.
Add bay leaf, cumin, paprika, tomatoes, tomato sauce, red pepper, chili powder, oregano and water as needed.
Simmer approximately 1 hour.
Add flour to thicken last 30 minutes.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Mix together 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Place a layer of apples in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 the sugar and cinnamon mix over the apples; cover with the remaining apples and then the other half of the sugar and cinnamon mix.

title: meatballs(modern)
directions: Measure out 1/4 cup soup combined with beef, bread crumbs, onion, parsley and egg.
Shape into meatballs 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Brown in skillet with shortening; blend remaining soup with water.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix Jell-O by directions on box.
Put in refrigerator to congeal.
Mix pineapple, pecans (sugar, if used) and salt.
When Jell-O is set, mix with 1 container of Cool Whip.
Add chilled pecan and pineapple mixture.
In large dish alternate layers starting with angel food cake which has been pinched in bite-size pieces.
Pour Jell-O mixture over cake until all is used.
Top with Cool Whip.
Then add frozen coconut on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Can put in punch bowl or oblong dish.

title: jiffy scallop casserole
directions: Thaw scallops if frozen.
Rinse thoroughly in cold water. Combine water and salt in 2-quart saucepan and bring to boil.
Add scallops; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 2 to 3 minutes, depending on size.
Drain.
Place beans and scallops in well-greased baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Cook onion in 2 tablespoons of oil until tender.
Add milk, soup, curry and pepper.
Heat, stirring, until well blended.
Pour over scallop mixture.
Combine crumbs, cheese and 1 tablespoon oil.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mrs. field's black and whites
directions: Mix together softened butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs.
Add remaining dry ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Add vanilla, semi-sweet and white chocolate bars.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 23 to 25 minutes.

title: angel food delight
directions: Crumble angel food cake.
Fold in cheese, sugar and Cool Whip. Mixture will be chunky.
Pour fruit on top.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: easy quick cobbler
directions: Put peaches in 9
x
13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and dry cake
mix.	Mix together.
Drizzle melted butter over all and sprinkle top
with cinnamon.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Can be served with ice cream.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, 4 cups flour and powdered sugar together.
Pat into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour onto baked crust. Bake 25 minutes longer.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Hollow out French bread.
Cut the leftover bread into shapes.
Pour dip into hollowed bread, use bread shapes to dip.

title: tomato and okra supreme
directions: Wash and slice okra; place okra in a pan or saucepan with a little water in bottom of pan for only a couple of minutes.
Stir in can of tomatoes, juice included.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until okra is cooked.
Thicken with a little flour if too runny.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, topping mix, milk and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy.
Pour into pie crusts.
Spread 1/2 cup coconut on each pie and chill.
Prepare instant pudding mix according to directions.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla; pour over cream cheese layer.
Garnish with whipped cream and toasted coconut.

title: white fruitcake
directions: Cream butter well; add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Beat eggs well and add.
Blend with cream mixture.
Chop fruits and nuts and mix with small amount of flour.
Sift remaining flour; fold in fruit and nuts.
Grease tube or loaf pan.
Pour in batter; put in cold oven and bake at 250° for 3 hours or loaf pan for 2 1/2 hours at 300°.
Cool in pan or on rack.
This cake can be frozen.
It makes a little less than 5 pounds.
No liquid other than the flavorings is needed.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients except cheese. Flour and grease pan.
Pour half the batter into pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese over batter.
Add rest of batter and put more grated cheese on top.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: chinese beef and rice(2 servings)
directions: Cook the rice and vegetable oil until rice is brown.
Then add the water, bouillon cube and the soy sauce.
Cook covered for 20 minutes.
Then simmer the onion, celery, green pepper and beef; simmer for 10 minutes more.
May need to add a little more water. All water should be absorbed at end of cooking time.

title: christmas jelly
directions: Grind the cranberries. Combine with strawberries and sugar. Cook over medium heat to boil. Boil 1 minute. Take off heat and add the pectin.
Stir well.
Let set 5 minutes. Skim off foam. Put in jars and seal.

title: snack nuts
directions: Put in pan and cook until all sugar and water disappears and is crystallized.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Shake every 10 minutes during baking period.

title: yellow layer cake
directions: Add 1/2 cup of the milk to the mix and beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining milk, eggs and vanilla; beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch layer pans or a 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes for layers or 35 minutes for 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in part of the water, add remaining water, strawberry jello and sugar.
Mix well.
Heat to boiling, boil one minute, stirring constantly to avoid scorching.
Cool.

title: apple muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin tins, large size muffins only use 6-muffin tin.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Turns brownish in color.
Place in muffin tin.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan.
Enjoy!

title: strawberry cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix by hand with wooden spoon until well blended.
Make small balls and roll them in powdered sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until bottoms are lightly browned.

title: marinated turkey breast with lemon caper sauce
directions: Use food processor with steel knife.
Place parsley in work bowl.
With machine running, drop garlic through feed tube and mince.
Add lemon juice, oil, rosemary, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper. Process 3 seconds to blend.
Transfer to large plastic bag.
Add turkey and seal airtight.
Marinate 4 hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator.
Bring to room temperature before continuing.

title: marshmallow icing(this is a sweet way to ice a cake.)
directions: In a saucepan, heat cream.
Add syrup and butter; heat well. Remove from heat and add powdered sugar and vanilla, mixing well until smooth.

title: raised waffles
directions: Put warm water and yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add milk, butter or oil, salt and sugar.
Beat flour, soda and eggs into milk, butter or oil, salt and sugar.
Cover the bowl.
Let stand overnight or at least 8 hours.
When time to cook, add 2 eggs, then 1/8 teaspoon soda.
Beat well.
Batter will be thin.
Spread over entire waffle iron.

title: irish whole meal brown bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and slowly add sour milk until mixture forms a doughy consistency.
Divide into 4 pieces.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Put cross on dough before baking.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook potatoes, chicken bouillon, celery margarine, salt and pepper until potatoes are done. Add flour, milk, and cheese and stir until thickened. Makes 6 servings.

title: mini mushroom quiche(serves six - to be prepared in muffin pan)
directions: Lightly grease each muffin cup with butter or margarine (spray vegetable coating can be used).
Roll pastry dough out to 1/16-inch thickness.
Cut six circles 5 1/2 to 6 inches in diameter.
Line each cup with a circle of dough, being careful not to stretch dough.
Trim and flute edges.
Prick sides and bottom of
each
shell
with
a fork.
Microwave on 2/3 power (Medium-high) for 4 to 6 minutes or until shells appear flaky. During cooking, rotate 2 to 3 times or as needed.
Set aside.

title: 6-day sweet pickles
directions: Wash the large cucumbers.
Pour boiling water over cucumbers, enough to cover them.
Let stand overnight.
Repeat 3 times (4 times total).
Drain and cut cucumbers into 1/2 to 3/4-inch chunks. Rinse.
Mix and bring the ingredients to a boil.
Put the cucumbers into the mix.
Take off heat.
Let stand for 2 days, stirring occasionally.
Bring all to a boil.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.
Additional processing in hot water bath for 5 minutes may be done.
Makes 10 to 12 pints.

title: apricot-cream cheese jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Set juice aside and reserve.
Mix jello with only 3 cups water.
Let jello cool.
Mix soft cream cheese with juice until real smooth and creamy.
When jello is cool, add cream cheese mixture through sieve.
Set in refrigerator until it starts to jell.
Add crushed drained pineapple.
Mix often until jelled.
When set, garnish with maraschino cherries and crushed nuts on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cool.
Pull apart and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Top with crushed crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: bacon cheese apple casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, place on paper towel to absorb fat. Mix apples, sugar and nutmeg.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Crumble bacon over apples.
Sprinkle cheese over bacon. Beat eggs, milk, and bisquick mix together.
Pour over apple, bacon, and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
A good breakfast or brunch casserole.
Serve warm.

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions thinly.
Saute onions in butter until very soft (do not brown).
In a casserole dish, place 1/2 of onions and 1/2 crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle thick with Parmesan cheese. Repeat onions, crackers and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble cooled cake into punch bowl.
Pour in pineapple.
Add pudding, bananas, pie filling and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: traditional trifle
directions: Break up the sponge cake or ladyfingers and spread with jam. Place in the bottom of glass dish (large).
Arrange fruit on top of sponge cake; set aside.
Make Jell-O; allow to cool a little, not yet firm, then spoon gently over sponge cake so that the Jell-O penetrates the sponge cake.
Put dish into the refrigerator; Jell-O needs to be set firm.
Meanwhile, make custard; allow to cool but not set, then spoon over the already set Jell-O.
Just before serving, spoon over the set custard the La Creme or whipped cream and decorate.

title: spam quickies
directions: Grind onion, Spam and cheese.
Mix together well.
Spread on deli-rye or half a hamburger bun.
Broil until cheese melts.
Great for parties, teenage treats or lunch.

title: praline sweet potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add sugar, eggs, margarine and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish.

title: montana fried chicken
directions: In medium bowl, put beaten egg, water and buttermilk.
Blend with whisk until well blended.
When blended, add paprika, allspice, ginger, black pepper and salt.
Whisk until blended again.
Put in chicken pieces and marinate 1 hour at room temperature.
A damp dish towel may be placed over the bowl to keep flies out.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Wash zucchini and blot dry.
Do not peel.
Cut off ends.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
In a skillet, heat 2 tablespoons diet margarine.
Saute zucchini over high heat until lightly browned. Be careful not to burn.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cover tightly and cook 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and spices and bring, uncovered, to a simmer.
Pour into a flat baking dish.
Sprinkle evenly with breadcrumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Melt remaining margarine and drizzle over entire surface.
Broil at 450° until crispy and browned.
Serve at once.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions, pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan and bake according to directions. When done, let cool. Place vanilla pudding on top of cake first.
Drain pineapple and put it on top of the pudding.
Spread whipped topping over the crushed pineapple.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Salt chicken; brown on top of stove in butter.
Mix rice, both cans of soup and water.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Brown the ground beef with the onion and garlic.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer one hour.

title: puffins
directions: In large bowl, combine shortening, sugar and egg and mix well. In small bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add to first mixture alternately with milk.
Grease muffin tins and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Immediately roll in melted butter, then in cinnamon sugar. Serve warm.
Makes 12 to 18 muffins.

title: apple spice tea
directions: Boil water; reduce heat.
Add tea bags, apple slices, cinnamon and sugar.
Let simmer 15 minutes.
Remove tea bags and apples. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: cole slaw (sweet)
directions: Mix and serve.
May add sugar or salt to taste.

title: potato pancakes(yield: 14)
directions: In a bowl, combine potatoes, eggs, flour, cream, salt and onion.
In a large skillet, melt half of butter.
Drop potato mixture by heaping tablespoonful into skillet and fry until golden brown on both sides.
Add butter to skillet as needed.

title: layered spaghetti bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat with green pepper and onion; drain.
Stir in dressing, tomato sauce, Parmesan cheese, oregano and black pepper.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes over low heat or until thoroughly heated.
Place 1/2 of the spaghetti in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 of the meat mixture and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Prepare rice as package directs.
Mix rice and remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with crushed chips. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender.
While noodles are boiling, brown ground beef.
Pour off excess oil.
Add chopped onion and the jars of Prego sauce.
Turn heat to medium-low.
When noodles are tender, rinse with cold water.

title: tomato, corn and green bean casserole
directions: Served at the June 1988 end-of-year church party.
This recipe can be easily expanded.

title: german skillet
directions: In frying pan with lid, layer with sauerkraut, hamburger, chopped onions, rice and on top the tomato sauce.
Cover and just simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: brenda's potato salad
directions: Boil and dice potatoes.
Boil and dice eggs.
Dice onion.
Fry and crumble bacon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cool and serve.

title: squash pickles
directions: Slice squash and soak in ice water 1 hour.
Mix sugar, vinegar, pepper, onion and spice and put in a pot and bring to a boil.
Drain squash and add to mixture and bring to a hard boil. Place in jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: baked devil eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise.
Remove the yolks and mash.
Mix with mayonnaise, paprika, curry powder and dry mustard.
Refill egg whites.
Place in baking dish, 10 1/2 x 6 x 1 1/2-inches.
Melt butter.
Blend in flour and add celery soup and milk.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add cheese.
Stir in curry powder.
Pour over eggs.

title: shrimp and pepper stir-fry(serves 4)
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
Dissolve chicken bouillon granules in the hot water.
Combine cornstarch and pepper.
Stir in lemon juice and soy sauce.
Stir in bouillon; set aside.

title: potato soup
directions: Simmer celery, carrots and onions in enough broth or water to cover until soft.
Add potatoes and broth or water to cover.
Add salt and white pepper.

title: cocoa fluff
directions: Beat all ingredients in chilled medium bowl until stiff.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Mix lightly with apples.
Pour into pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan.
Dot with butter.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust.
Serve warm.

title: blackened fish
directions: Heat a large cast-iron skillet over very high heat until it is beyond the smoking stage and you see white ash in the skillet bottom.
The skillet must heat at least 10 minutes.
I find using a gas grill works best for this.
Coat both sides of fish generously with seasoning, patting it in by hand.
Place fish in skillet and pour 1 to 2 teaspoons melted butter on top of each fillet.
(Be careful; butter may flare up.)
Cook uncovered until the underside looks charred (2 to 4 minutes).
Turn fish over; top again with melted butter and cook until done (2 minutes).
Serve immediately with extra butter, if desired.

title: buttery crescents
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in milk.
Add 4 cups flour, eggs, butter, sugar and salt; beat until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch the dough down and divide in thirds.
Roll each portion into a 12-inch circle; cut each circle into 12 wedges.
Roll up wedges from the wide end and place with pointed end down on greased baking sheets. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush with butter if desired.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water and let cool to room temperature. Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add chocolate and vanilla.
Sift flour with baking powder and add melted chocolate and buttermilk alternately to it. You will need to make 4 or 5 separate additions.
Beat just until barely smooth after each addition - be careful not to overbeat.
Stir in coconut and chopped nuts.
Turn batter into 3 greased 8 inch layer cake pans and bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 20 - 25 minutes, or until straw inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from oven and let stand in pans for 10 minutes, then turn out on rack to cool.

title: granger cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, brown sugar, shortening, margarine, eggs, vanilla, salt and baking powder; mix well.
Add flour, baking soda, Rice Krispies, oats, pecans and coconut.
Hint:
This recipe is very dry; do not add liquid.

title: applewood julep
directions: Mix and serve over ice.
Serves 6.

title: cheese topped tuna
directions: Toast bread; lay tuna on slice. Top with vegetables, then cheese. Broil until cheese is melted.

title: spinach salad
directions: Serve with sweet and sour dressing.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Cream ingredients.
Stir in rhubarb.
Put in 9-inch pie crust. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and beat several minutes on high with an electric mixer.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 minutes at 325° or until set.
Cool!
Top with whipped cream or ice cream to serve.
Makes 1 pie.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Brown the meat; drain the fat.
Stir in the onions, salt, bread crumbs, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and sour cream.
Slice zucchini thin lengthwise. Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange half of the slices in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Add meat mixture, then cover with rest of zucchini slices.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and put Mozzarella slices and last tablespoon of Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake, uncovered, 10 more minutes.

title: cream enchiladas
directions: Brown meats; add other ingredients and simmer until all are melted.
Serve over chips and top with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix well 2 instant vanilla pudding and sour cream.
Add crushed pineapple with juice.
Mix well.
Blend in Cool Whip and chill before serving.

title: quick stuffed pork chops
directions: Mix Stove Top stuffing in a bowl (do not cook) according to package directions.
Cut pocket in each pork chop.
Fill with stuffing mix.
Coat with Shake 'n Bake.
Place on wire rack in shallow baking pan and bake 45 minutes at 350° or until brown and crusty.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until tender.
Peel and shred. Combine potatoes, sour cream, onions, 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Put in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.
May be assembled early and refrigerated (add 10 minutes to baking time).

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together the first 2 ingredients; spread in long dish (put a little aside to garnish top).
Mix together the next 4 ingredients; beat until stiff like whipped cream.
Spread 1/2 of mixture on top of crumbs, then spread cherry pie filling.
Spread other half of cream on top of cherries.
Sprinkle leftover crumbs on top.
Let chill 4 hours or more.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Add all
dry
ingredients
to
potatoes.
Combine eggs, milk and melted	margarine
to potato mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven about 40 minutes
or
until done in center.
Add lemon or vanilla flavoring, if desired.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs and oleo together.
Mix with other ingredients and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potatoes au gratin (microwave)
directions: Slice potatoes thinly.
Add onion, salt, and pepper to taste. Dot with butter. Cook on high 5 minutes.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Brown linguica, drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients except half the cheese.
Mix well.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package directions. Pour into a 9 x 13 inch pan. While cake is hot, punch holes all over the top with a fork. Mix cream of coconut with the Eagle Brand milk. Pour over hot cake. Cool cake. Spread cool whip to cover top. Sprinkle coconut over Cool Whip. Refrigerate. Better made a day or two ahead.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a greased sheet cake pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Shape into small meatballs.
Place on jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with sides. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until evenly brown.
(This is easier than frying.)
Drain on paper towels.

title: maude's old fashioned molasses taffy
directions: Combine ingredients.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves and mixture starts to boil.
Increase to medium heat and boil for about 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture appears to smoke.
Pour onto well-greased (butter or margarine) cookie sheet.

title: sand cups
directions: Pour milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping and half of crushed cookies. Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies into cups.
Fill cups 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Decorate.

title: roast potatoes with rosemary
directions: Brush potatoes with olive oil. Sprinkle with garlic powder, rosemary and black pepper. Arrange, cut side up, in shallow roasting pan. Pour 1/4 cup water in bottom of pan.
Roast at 375° for 40 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings. Approximate Nutritional Content Per Potato:
129 total calories, 3 g protein, 25 g carbohydrates, 0 mg cholesterol, 2 g fat, 4 mg sodium.

title: chicken-n-biscuit casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done, let cool.
Pull chicken off the bone. Take biscuits and roll them out.
Wrap chicken up in biscuits and place in glass pan.
In saucepan, melt cheese with milk, cream of chicken and biscuits.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake until done.

title: lemon-tarragon chicken
directions: Melt butter on medium heat.
Add chicken, mushrooms, garlic, sherry, tarragon and lemon pepper seasoning.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, turning once. Remove chicken and mushrooms.

title: honey butter
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending well.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Makes 1 cup.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1/2 cake in large pieces in bottom of punch bowl. Spread and layer following ingredients: 1/2 pudding, 1 can cherry pie filling, 1 can peaches (drained) and 1/2 cup chopped pecans. Add rest of cake, crumbled, and rest of ingredients:
1/2 pudding, 1 can cherry pie filling, 1 can peaches (drained) and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Top all this with Cool Whip.
Makes a full bowl. Put in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: nutty-chicken-rice salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl; mix well. Combine next 6 ingredients; stirring well.
Add to chicken mixture and toss gently.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all the ingredients and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Blend until creamy, about 3 minutes on medium speed.
Blend in egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls, 3-inches apart, on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes (they will appear light and moist; do not overbake).
Cool on baking sheet for 2 minutes. Remove to cooling rack.

title: classic apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry and let rest while you prepare apples.
Slice apples into large bowl and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg to apples; mix well.
On a lightly floured board, roll out half of pie pastry to a 12-inch circle.
Place in bottom of a 9-inch pan and, using fingers, gently press dough to side of pan.
Trim any overlapping edges of dough.
Mix apples again with large spoon and turn into pastry-lined pan.
Dot surface with the butter.

title: frozen raspberry salad
directions: Mix honey and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in loaf pan and freeze until ready to serve.

title: "babe's" old fashion stew
directions: Mix the above into the skillet of fried stew meat and simmer (don't boil) 1 1/2 hours or until the vegetables are tender.

title: norwegian kringler
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients like a pie crust.
Put on a cookie sheet in 2 long strips, 3-inches wide.
Put the 1 cup water and 1/2 cup butter in a saucepan and heat to boiling point.
As you take from the stove, add 1 cup flour.
Stir until smooth; then beat in 3 eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth after each.
Add 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Spread lightly on the dough strips and bake 45 minutes in a 375° oven.
When cool, frost with the powdered sugar, cream, 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon almond extract.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple into saucepan; bring to a boil and mix with both packages of jello. Dissolve jello 5 to 10 minutes. Mix jello and cream cheese using a mixer. Put into big bowl and add Coca-Cola. Mix pineapple, cherries and nuts with mixture and pour into mold. Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: shrimp dip mold (dip)
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in cold water.
Heat soup and add gelatine, stirring until melted.
Add other ingredients.
Place in mold until firm.
Unmold and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Slice zucchini.
Let stand overnight in enough water to cover, plus 5 tablespoons salt.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Boil 30 minutes.
Can and seal.

title: john's texas chili
directions: Brown beef; drain off grease.
Add onions, garlic, jalapenos, chili powder, celery salt and pepper.
Cook this until onions are clear.
Add green chilies, tomatoes, tomato sauce and V-8 juice. Cook mixture for 2 hours on simmer.

title: busch's grove bellevue dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until smooth.
Makes 3 3/4 cups.

title: dorito dip
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Mix in refried beans and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix in taco sauce and Colby cheese.
Simmer 15 minutes. Serve hot with Doritos for dipping.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine the flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda and mix thoroughly.
Pour the water over the dry ingredients and add the vanilla and salad dressing.
Mix these ingredients well and place in a greased baking pan.
Bake your cake in a preheated oven at 300° to 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.
This is a very moist cake and keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: chili
directions: In a frying pan brown ground beef with chopped onion and green pepper.
Strain all grease and transfer to large stewing pot.
Add all remaining ingredients and cover the pot.
Cook on medium-high heat for one hour.
Stir frequently.

title: cherry cheesecake(fat-free)
directions: Beat cheeses 2 minutes, until blended. Add lemon juice, milk and sugar substitute; beat 1 minute or until smooth. Fold in topping. Spoon into crust; cover and chill. Top with cherry pie filling.

title: hamburger in a pea patch
directions: Brown ground
beef; pour off drippings.
Blend in gravy mix, garlic salt,
water
and
uncooked	rice.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat
to
low.
Cover.
Simmer
15	minutes.
Stir	in thawed peas, water chestnuts or mushrooms.
Continue to simmer until rice is	tender.
Stir in onions.
Serve with soy sauce. Serves 4 to 6.

title: green goddess salad dressing
directions: Mix, blend and chill all ingredients.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and apples.
Sift together and stir into apple mixture the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well and add chopped nuts and raisins.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
When almost cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: shipwreck
directions: Mix together in buttered casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 250° to 300° for 1 1/2 hours or more.

title: german rouladen
directions: Spread mustard over roast beef.
Top with the following: chopped boiled eggs, chopped pickle and a slice of bacon.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Saute in oil until nice and brown. Put oil and meat in pot and just cover with water.
Cook one hour on top of stove at medium heat.
Mix 2 gravy mixes and 2 tablespoons flour.
Sprinkle over water.
Cook until nice and thick.

title: frozen bananas
directions: You will need 6 wooden sticks.

title: tapioca jello delight
directions: Mix dry puddings with Jell-O.
Add water.
Cook until it boils.
Remove from heat and add drained fruit and Cool Whip. Serve cold after it sets.

title: corn fritters
directions: Heat 2 to 3-inches oil in 375° heavy skillet.
Pour liquid from corn into medium bowl. Add egg and biscuit mix.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in corn.
Drop tablespoonfuls of batter into hot oil. Fry to golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel. Serve hot with syrup.
Makes 24 fritters.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots; add water and cook in covered pan until just tender, about 10 minutes, then drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to carrots; cook until sauce is clear and thickened.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Refrigerate for 1 hour and serve.

title: zip quick cherry crisp
directions: Pour filling into 8-inch pie shell or into pan without shell. Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Pour melted butter or margarine over all.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and place in casserole dish.
Slice margarine and place on top evenly.

Bake for approximately 45 minutes or until browned and squash is tender. (Not cooking the squash first gives the casserole more flavor.) Also, if it is not creamy enough to suit, add another can of cream of chicken soup.

title: rocky road
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add marshmallows and peanuts.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch square pan lined with wax paper.
Put in refrigerator for a couple of hours.

title: cabbage beef stew
directions: Put all together in large pot and cook down.

title: christmas candy
directions: Melt Almond Bark and peanut butter together in heavy saucepan. Stir constantly.
Pour over remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by tsp. on waxed paper.

title: california lemonade
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a 2-quart pitcher.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together and place in a greased casserole dish.
Place topping on sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pink dip
directions: Pour salsa into bowl.
Add cream cheese.
Mix with electric mixer until creamy.
Add more salsa if needed.
Serve with your favorite chips.

title: thanksgiving rice
directions: Boil rice; set aside in colander.
Use a large skillet to cook sausage thoroughly.
Saute celery, onions and pepper in sausage fat.
When vegetables are lightly browned, add the rice.
Stir well for about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; put into a large mixing bowl.
Combine with egg and seasonings.
Mix well.
Put into greased casserole dishes for serving or freezing.
Reheat in oven until rice is hot.
Yield:
12 to 14 servings.

title: runderlapjes(dutch beef stew)
directions: Put butter in saucepan; bring up to temperature.
Add meat, seal juices and fry golden.
Add onions, bay leaf, cloves and thyme and fry slowly.
Add flour and allow to brown slightly.
Add all other ingredients.
Transfer to casserole, cover with lid and cook in a slow oven, gas mark 3 (325°), for about 1 1/2 hours (or until tender).
Garnish with parsley and serve with boiled potatoes and red cabbage.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly, then mix in the cornmeal and eggs, beating each egg in separately.
Add other ingredients and pile filling as high as possible in an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Cook in a 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until filling is set.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve pie hot or at room temperature.
Or use filling for 6 individual tart shells to be baked about 25 minutes.

title: instant fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts, in iron skillet.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat vigorously until cool and beginning to thicken.
Stir in nuts.
Pour on buttered pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix water drained from whole kernel corn with corn bread mix in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: mcdonna's sandwich sauce
directions: Chop or shred lettuce.
Mix all ingredients together in a small bowl.
You may need to add just a small amount more of salad dressing.
Great on hamburgers!

title: spiced steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces (6).
Mix flour, salt, pepper and pound this mixture into steak.
Heat Crisco in skillet. Add steak and brown on each side.

title: leek and zucchini gratin
directions: Cut the leeks into quarters lengthwise, then into lengths of approximately 2 1/2-inches. Blanch in boiling, salted water for 2 to 3 minutes. Drain thoroughly and keep warm. Cut the zucchini into narrow strips or thin slices and blanch for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes and then drain thoroughly. Melt the butter in a nonstick pan and toss in first the leeks and then the zucchini. Heat for 2 to 3 minutes, shaking the pan frequently and stirring carefully to prevent them breaking up. Season well. Turn into a flameproof dish; spoon over the cream and then sprinkle with a mixture of crumbs and grated cheese. Place under a fairly low broiler (grill) for a few minutes, until lightly browned. Serve sprinkled with finely chopped red bell pepper. Serves 4.

title: swiss steak
directions: Flour steak and brown lightly in skillet.
Place browned steak in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place 1 bell pepper ring and 1 onion ring on each steak portion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour 1 large can tomatoes over steak and add water.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: mexican beef and chip casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef into 1-quart glass casserole.
Add onion and garlic.
Microwave, uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes or until meat is set.
Stir to break up meat; drain fat.
Stir in soup and chilies.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and fit into a cookie sheet making sure all seams and perforations are sealed.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and let cool completely.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash.
Drain.
Layer bottom of dish with crumbs. Alternate layers of squash and cheese.
Top with crumbs.
Fill with milk.
Put butter on top.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: molasses muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add molasses.
Combine soda and buttermilk; add to mixture, blending well.
Combine flour and spices, add to molasses mixture.
Stir in raisins, mix well.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook the spaghetti according to package directions (you should have
about
cups of cooked spaghetti).
Stir butter into hot spaghetti.
Stir
in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture
into
a
"crust"
in a buttered 10-inch pie plate. Spread cottage cheese over the bottom of the spaghetti "crust". Brown
ground meat and combine with spaghetti sauce. Turn
meat mixture into spaghetti "crust." Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven
for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine base ingredients. Mix at low speed until crumbly.
Press in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until light golden brown; cool.

title: molded salad
directions: Pour hot water over cheese and Jell-O; mix well with egg beater.
Add pineapple (drained).
Cool until slightly thickened. Add Cool Whip; fold in Jell-O.
Add cherries and nuts, if desired.

title: eclair cake
directions: Boil together margarine and water; add flour and beat with fork.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Could use portable mixer to whip it.
Spread evenly in greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: tamale pie
directions: Place meat in a skillet.
Season meat with seasoned salt and pepper (at your own discretion).
Brown meat, then drain the grease from it.
Next, with meat in skillet, add dry taco seasoning mix. Add 1 cup water; stir together.
Add corn.
Let this come to a boil, then lower heat to medium for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: posh pasta
directions: Cook the macaroni and drain.
Toss with the Parmesan Dressing. Add the remaining ingredients. Cover and chill.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: banana or pumpkin bread
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together; add rest of ingredients, blending well.
Bake in 3 loaf pans or three 1 pound coffee cans at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy.
Add milk, juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Top with pie filling.
Cover with whipped cream before serving.

title: molasses baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook for 2 hours at 250°.

title: rice and corn casserole
directions: Saute
onions
and mix all together.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Combine shortening and sugar; cream with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating 30 seconds after each addition. Stir 1 c. flour into creamed mixture until blended. Combine buttermilk, soda, salt, lemon extract, vanilla extract and butter flavoring; stir one-half of buttermilk mixture into creamed mixture until blended. Stir 1 c. flour into creamed mixture. Repeat procedure, ending with flour. Pour batter into a well greased and floured 10 inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and pour into 9 X 9 greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pina colada ring
directions: Soften kosher gelatin in pineapple juice; heat to dissolve. Pour into blender container.
Add Neufchatel cheese, sugar, rinds and rum extract.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into large bowl.
Chill until mixture mounds from a spoon.
Place nonfat dry milk, ice water and lemon juice in small mixer bowl.
Beat at high speed until stiff peaks form, 4 to 6 minutes.
Fold into kosher gelatin mixture.
Spoon into 6-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm. Unfold onto serving platter.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut. Garnish outer edge and center of mold with fresh fruit.
Makes 6 cups.

title: busy day cake
directions: Mix white cake mix, milk and eggs and pour on sheet cake pan. Bake 20 minutes.
While still hot, punch holes all over and pour coconut cream on top and let cool.
Spread Cool Whip on top and shredded coconut over all.
This is really delicious and very moist!

title: st. paul rice
directions: Combine soup mix, water and rice; cook for 7 minutes.
Add bell pepper, onion, celery, almonds and drained sausage meat.
Mix well and place into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat in pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° and cool.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and spread for next layer.
Mix the next 2 ingredients and spread for third layer.
Spread the next 2 ingredients for fourth layer. Sprinkle with few more pecans.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: cornstarch pudding
directions: Put
milk
in
double
boiler
and
get it hot.
Make a paste, then add to your hot milk and stir until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: watermelon punch
directions: In a large bowl, blend all ingredients and chill.
Serve in scalloped watermelon boat.
Makes 14 (3/4-cup) servings.

title: dropped  cookies molasses
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles; rinse with cold water and drain.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Mix dressing and pour over salad; chill one hour before serving.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Make soft dough.
Roll out in 8-inch squares.
Brush with melted butter.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on dough. Roll up and cut in 1-inch pieces.
Combine butter and brown sugar in 8-inch dish.
Spread/scatter nuts over mixture.
Arrange rolls on top.
Microwave 6 minutes and invert.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix butter, salt, pepper and flour.
Cook until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat until boiling. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Mix with cooked macaroni.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Fry sausage and drain all grease off.
Thaw bread.
Roll out onto large circle shape.
Mix eggs and 1/2 can Parmesan cheese; spread this over dough.
Scatter sausage over the top.
Place Mozzarella cheese next and remaining Parmesan cheese, but 1 tablespoon.
Roll dough into log.
Set on counter and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt margarine; drizzle over top of baked bread.
Top with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese. Place back in oven long enough to brown.
Serve warm.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Mix ingredients in a skillet.
Cook over medium heat until mixture pulls away from sides of pan and becomes doughy in consistency.
Knead until cool.
Model different colors of dough into shapes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package; drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add cheese, celery, mayonnaise and onions.
Mix and put in casserole dish.
Mix margarine and cracker crumbs; sprinkle over top.
Bake in a 350° oven until crackers are brown.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil Macaroni until tender (10-15 min).
Put into medium size baking dish.
Add margarine - stir until melted.
Add milk
Stir in salt, pepper, and onion powder.
Stir in cheese, reserving some for on top.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Wipe ribs with damp paper towels.
Place ribs in a single layer in a roasting pan.
Roast ribs at 450° for 20 minutes, turning once.
Prepare basting sauce:
Mix all ingredients together.

title: sweet potato patties
directions: In bowl, combine potatoes and egg; add all other ingredients, mixing well together.
Shape into patties about 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
Brown both sides in melted butter on medium heat.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13 or two 8-inch square pans.
Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Mix well.
Spread thin layer of batter in bottom of pan. Mix together the brown sugar, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Sprinkle half of this over batter.
Spoon rest of batter over, then cover with remaining topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool slightly, then mix powdered sugar and milk; drizzle over top.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients for 1 minute.
Pour over dry oatmeal; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Refrigerate until cool.

title: divinely decadent cake
directions: In large saucepan, bring corn syrup and butter to a boil; stir well and remove from heat.
Add chocolate; stir until melted, then add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Slowly blend in flour and nuts. Pour in greased and floured 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: ham rolls
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions on box. Add a can of tuna and serve!

title: rice pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: carrot salad 2
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill well.
Serve as a side dish.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Wash and sort cranberries.
Put into saucepan with 2 cups water.
Cook over low heat until cranberry skins pop, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Force cranberries through sifter. Stir until it purees.
Add 3/4 cups of sugar and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Return to heat and bring to boil, cooking about 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cool and chill thoroughly in refrigerator.
Remove from refrigerator and add 2 cups chilled pineapple juice and 1/2 cup chilled orange juice. Makes about 6 servings.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the first 4 ingredients in a bowl and beat with mixer at medium speed until well blended (about 3 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Lightly spoon flour into dry measuring cups; level with a knife.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients (flour through nutmeg), stirring with a whisk.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to sugar mixture; beat well after each addition.
Stir in apple and brandy, if desired.

title: coagulated porridge(chao huyet)
directions: Boil rice, shrimp and broth in a large saucepan on medium heat for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add coagulated blood in portages and cook for approximately 30 minutes on low heat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for approximately 15 minutes on low heat.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 small bowl servings.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter and pour in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts in pan.
Place 1 package dough balls (still frozen) over nuts.
Mix vanilla pudding, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour this over dough.
Melt 1/2 cup of butter and pour over this.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let sit 10 minutes and remove.

title: almond bar chocolate(sauce)
directions: In small heavy saucepan, stir together chocolate and milk. Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted.
Serve warm over cake, ice cream or other desserts, or use as a dip for fresh fruit.

title: christmas hard candy
directions: Cook in deep pan.
Stir together until mixture comes to a rolling boil and sugar has dissolved.
Then allow to cook until mixture reaches hard crack stage.
Use candy thermometer or a drop in cool water will form shape of a drop and be very hard and easy to crack.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon oil of flavor and food coloring (to desired color).

title: salmon dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, onion, ketchup and horseradish until well mixed.
Fold in salmon and mix well.
Serve with Pepperidge Farm sesame snack sticks.

title: icebox chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat in 9 x 13 pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Spread on crust. Mix puddings and milk. Mix and spread on cream cheese layer. Cover top with rest of Cool Whip. Grate chocolate on top.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Mix the first three ingredients together and chill.
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.
This makes a clear punch and sparkles.
Great for holidays.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease roaster or heavy skillet.
Combine and put in roaster the first 7 ingredients in the order given.
Season the chicken with salt, pepper, sage and poultry seasoning.
Dip each piece in bag with seasoning.
Lay each piece of chicken on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Add water at this time if the cooked dish is getting too dry to continue cooking for another 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown rice in melted margarine.
Add soup and 1/2 cup water. Cook as directed (about 20 minutes on top of stove).

title: cajun dressing
directions: Brown sausage, stirring to crumble; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Place in large casserole or 2 medium size.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover for 15 to 20 extra minutes. Freezes well.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown beef.
Put in casserole and cover with sauce.
Cook in slow oven (300°) for 3 hours (or cook in crock-pot for 10 hours on low).

title: potato gnocci with gorgonzola sauce
directions: Fresh gnocci can be found at most grocery stores. Fix according to package directions.

title: crisp pastel cookies
directions: Mix the shortening, sugar, jello, eggs and vanilla. Blend in dry ingredients.
Roll dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten each with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: corporation stew
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
At least 1 hour before serving, add carrots, green beans, whole potatoes or any vegetable desired.
Can be served over rice or noodles or as a stew or soup.
Delicious!

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Thoroughly combine eggs, sugar, butter or margarine, lemon juice and vanilla; stir in coconut.
Pour filling into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool before serving.
Garnish with whipped cream and toasted coconut, if desired.

title: busy day tuna casserole
directions: Crush potato chips medium coarse.
Add rest of ingredients and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Should be a little brown on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in cereal. Combine banana, milk, egg and oil.
Add mixture stirring just until flour is moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tester inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on rack. Makes 1 loaf.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat dough into ungreased 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned; cool.
In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping. Spread over crust.
Arrange fruit on top.
Round kiwi fruit and grapes on first, then bananas and then mandarin oranges.

title: walnut raspberry brownies(super moist - for raspberry lovers.)
directions: Melt chocolate with shortening over warm water.
Cool slightly.
Blend eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: orange sauce
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil. Cook, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat; let cool completely.
Fold in whipped cream.
Serve over pound cake. Yields 2 cups.

title: play dough
directions: Cook over low heat until mixture forms a ball.
Let cool. Knead in a little more flour, if needed.
Store in airtight container in a cool place.

title: salmon croutons
directions: Mix salmon, eggs and buttermilk together.
Crumble in crackers, salt and pepper.
Mix together well.
Crumble crackers on plate.
Roll into ball, then roll in cracker crumbs.
Cook in deep fryer until brown.

title: chicken liver and bacon roll-ups
directions: Dip chicken livers lightly in mustard.
Wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around each and secure with toothpick.
Coat livers with crumbs.
Place in 8-inch square baking dish and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pork tenderloin with cream sauce
directions: Saute the tenderloin in the oil in a skillet until lightly colored on all sides.
Add the chicken broth and place in a 350° oven for an hour.
Remove the tenderloin from the skillet and keep warm.
To the juices in the skillet, add the sherry or Madeira and shallots or onion; boil until the juices thicken some.
Mix the flour with the cream or milk and stir into the pan juices until the mixture thickens slightly.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Slice the tenderloin.
Pour the sauce over the meat. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Serves 6.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Put yeast in very warm water for a few minutes.
Add all ingredients together and mix.
Let stand in an oiled bowl for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Grease a large cookie sheet and separate dough and shape into rolls.
Place on sheet.
Makes 12 to 14 rolls. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: star salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in frozen raspberries.
Break up cranberry with a fork and stir into Jell-O mixture.
Chill until partially set.
Carefully pour in soda, stirring gently.
Turn into 6-cup mold.
Chill overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add zucchini and mix.
Fold in dry ingredients and nuts.
Spoon into two greased and floured loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: watergate salad(good summer dish)
directions: Mix all ingredients together including pineapple juice.
Let stand in refrigerator over night.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt, baking powder, oil, milk, eggs, grated cheese, corn and chopped onion.
Pour into large skillet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; let cool just enough to handle. Peel and dice potatoes while warm. Dice peppers, onion and celery with salt and pepper to taste. Add vinegar and oil; mix well. Cool in refrigerator. Next day, add sour cream and mayo.

title: arroz amarillo con pollo(yellow rice and chicken)
directions: Cut fryers in quarters.
In a large skillet, heat oil and saute chicken slowly until just pale golden in color.
Remove to casserole with cover (earthenware is preferable).

title: skewered steak dinner
directions: Toss beef and dressing in glass or plastic bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour but no longer than 8 hours, turning beef occasionally.
Remove beef from marinade.
Reserve marinade. Thread beef alternately with onion and bell pepper on 6-inch metal skewers, leaving 1/4 inch between each piece.
Place 1 cherry tomato on the end of each skewer.
Brush kabobs generously with marinade.
Cover and grill kabobs 4 to 5 inches from medium coals 15 to 20 minutes for medium doneness.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Mix each package of Jell-O separately with 1 1/2 cups hot water and place in shallow pans separately and place in refrigerator to set.
When set, then slice in small cubes or larger cubes.
Mix 2 envelopes Knox gelatine with 1/2 cup cold water and let stand for 5 minutes, then add 1/2 cup boiling water and mix well.
In another bowl, mix the 4x sugar with pineapple juice, then mix in the Knox gelatine.
Beat whipping cream until thick and fold into the gelatine with the Jell-O.
Pour into angel food pan and refrigerate.

title: different bread pudding
directions: Butter bottom and sides of upper part of double boiler.
Pour in brown sugar.
Butter bread and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cut into small cubes and place on top of sugar.

title: charleston oyster pie
directions: Place a layer
of oysters in a casserole dish.	Crumble over this a
few
saltines;
repeat
for
second
layer.
Pour milk, dry white
wine,
eggs
and water, beaten together, over layers until milk	mixture has completely covered top.
Season to taste. Bake at 375° until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Day Ahead:
Cut chicken wing in 3 segments, discarding wing tips.
Place in baking dish.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over wings.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: electric blender cheesecake
directions: Line an 8-inch layer cake pan with seasoned crumbs.
Into container of electric blender put eggs, sugar, vanilla and sour cream.
Cover and blend on high speed for 15 seconds.
With motor on, gradually add cheese and melted butter.
Pour into prepared pan and bake in pre-heated 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until set in center.
The filling will be soft, but it will firm as the cake cools.
Chill before serving.

title: salmon bake
directions: Toss salmon, stuffing croutons, parsley and onion together in a bowl.
Blend eggs, condensed soup, milk and pepper.
Add to salmon mixture and mix thoroughly.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Garnish center with overlapping quarter slices of lemon and parsley. Serve with hot sour cream sauce.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: party punch base
directions: In a small saucepan, combine water, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer covered for 10 minutes.
Chill.
Strain and discard spices.
Combine with fruit juices.
To serve, combine base with club soda or with wine, brandy or other flavorings.
Makes 12 (5 ounce) servings.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Spread package cookie dough on pizza pan.
Bake according to package directions.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Brown hamburger, chop up and drain grease.
Dice onion and mango.
Add all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook 2 hours on high. Longer on low.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Let come to a boil (do not boil).
Put in jars and seal while hot.
Yields 8 pints.

title: potato leaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan; set aside.
In a blender puree cottage cheese for 1 minute or until smooth.

title: italian meatballs and sauce
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Shape into balls and saute in a small amount of oil.

title: 100% whole wheat bread
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, honey, oil, salt and eggs.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat 100 strokes by hand or 3 to 4 minutes with electric mixer.
Cover bowl; let sponge rise until double.
Mix in remaining flour, 1 cup at a time; knead thoroughly for 8 to 10 minutes.
Oil both; let rise 4 times (every 20 minutes, punch it).
Shape into loaves.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican fruit punch
directions: Cut papaya, banana and apples into chunks.
Process with sugar, cinnamon and ice water in blender until smooth and creamy. Yields 10 servings.

title: scotch meat loaves(cannonballs)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine beaten egg, bread crumbs, celery, onion, salt, sage and garlic powder.
Add ground beef; mix well. Shape half of each mixture around each peeled, hard-cooked egg. Arrange meat loaves in a baking dish.
Combine chili sauce, parsley, water and oregano; pour over meat loaves.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spoon chili sauce mixture over loaves; top each with cheese.
Return to oven and heat until cheese melts.
Makes 2 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, lemon juice, eggs, sour cream and bananas.
Sift salt, flour, soda and baking powder.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until inserted tester comes out clean.

title: laila's crystal cream
directions: Dissolve each flavored gelatin in 1 1/2 cups hot water separately.
Place each in separate pan to mold. When firm, cut into squares.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put yogurt in bowl.
Put all breading ingredients in tightly sealed plastic bag.
Roll chicken in yogurt.
Put in bag and shake to coat.
Put breaded chicken on baking sheet sprayed with nonstick spray.
Lightly spray chicken with vegetable oil.
Bake for 1 hour, turning every 20 minutes to brown evenly.

title: banana oat bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all dry ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: monkey bread(caramel biscuit ring)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease 12 cup fluted tube pan. In small saucepan, combine brown sugar, nuts, margarine and water.
Heat until margarine melts.

title: pizza dough
directions: Stir yeast and sugar into water.
Let stand about 10 minutes or until foamy.
Put yeast mixture and eggs in a large bowl.
Add flour and salt; stir or beat until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface and knead 5 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Put dough into a large oiled bowl and turn down to oil top.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap.
Let dough rise in a warm draft-free place 1 hour or until doubled.

title: low-fat chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Melt margarine in non-stick skillet.
Cook onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in green chilies, sour cream and soup; mix well.

title: shrimp marinara
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add garlic, sauteing until golden.
Add parsley, shrimp and cayenne.
Cook for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add wine; cover, cooking an additional 3 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients; cover and cook 10 minutes. Serve hot over rice.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a large pot, melt butter.
Add onions and leeks.
Saute over moderate heat until they are soft, approximately 15 minutes. Add chicken stock and broccoli (washed and chopped).
Cover and simmer until broccoli is tender, about 10 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugars, oleo and oil until blended.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until creamy.
Mix together the flour, soda, powder, salt and cream of tartar.
Add to mixture.
Chill 1 hour. Roll out and cut or roll into balls and flatten on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until light brown.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, Kool-Aid and sugar in the hot water.
Add cold water and pour into 4-ounce paper cups.
Cover with foil, sticking a popsicle stick into the middle of the foil.

title: drunken meatballs
directions: Combine meat and seasonings.
Form into bite size meatballs. Heat water, ketchup and beer in a large saucepan; carefully drop meatballs into liquid.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve in sauce in chafing dish.
Yields 50 to 55 meatballs.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: No substitutes!
Use real butter and real chocolate chips! And real vanilla extract!

title: easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in reserved broth from cooking the chicken. Drain off most of the broth when spaghetti is done.
Cube chicken and add while spaghetti is hot, stirring to mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Cover and bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: crispy cheese wafers
directions: Gradually add flour, pepper, cheese and softened butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Fold in 2 cups Rice Krispies into mixture by hand.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls and put on ungreased baking sheet; flatten with fork.
Bake 14 minutes at 300°.
Cool on paper towel.
Makes about 6 or 8 dozen.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients (except lemon-lime drink) well and freeze. Let thaw for 3 hours.
Put in punch bowl; add lemon-lime drink just before serving.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Break chocolate into pieces.
In saucepan, combine milk, chocolate and marshmallows.
Cook over low heat, stirring until chocolate and marshmallows are melted.

title: easy herb biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and pour in a greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bavarian cold slaw
directions: Mix salt in cabbage and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Heat sugar and vinegar in saucepan; set aside and cool.
Mix celery, bell peppers and carrots with cabbage.
Pour vinegar and sugar over it and seal tightly.
Refrigerate.
Will keep up to 6 weeks.

title: biscochitos("new mexican cookies")
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Dip tops of cookies in cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: bean soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook.
When cooking on stove, double water.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and 2 teaspoons salt. Add Crisco and mix with a pastry blender until ingredients are crumbly.

In a separate bowl, beat the vinegar, egg and water together with a fork. Combine the two mixtures, stirring with a fork, until moistened. Divide the dough into 5 equal portions. Shape each into a flat patty for rolling. Wrap each patty in plastic wrap and chill for at least 30 minutes or overnight. When ready to roll out, flour each side and roll out.
Makes 5 to 7 crusts.
Patties will keep for up to a week in refrigerator.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil bouillon cubes, water, celery, carrots, potatoes and onions for 20 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables; cook until tender. Add soup, water and cheese.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Serves 8.

title: polske paczki
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Add 2 cups flour, let stand in warm place 30 minutes.
Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla, grated rind of orange or lemon and scant teaspoon of salt until light.
Add this to the sponge.
Melt butter and add this to the sponge.
Add 5 cups flour, cover and allow to rise for about one hour or until double in bulk.
When light, turn on floured board and pat with hands until dough is one-half an inch in thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter, cover and let rise again until light.
Drop in deep hot fat and fry until done.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Combine oleo, sugar and egg yolks and cook 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, pecan pieces, dates (cut in small pieces) and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Make into balls and roll in coconut.
