title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Ice with chocolate butter cream icing or your favorite canned icing.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt bag of chocolate chips and spread over mixture.
Refrigerate. Cut when hardened.

title: marie's pizza
directions: Cook ground beef and add tomato sauce and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir Bisquick, egg and milk to a soft dough.
Spread 1/2 of the dough in greased pan (dish pan).
Pour remaining can of tomato sauce over dough, spreading evenly.
Layer 4 slices of cheese, the meat mixture, mushrooms, remaining cheese slices and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with remaining dough.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: mama's ham loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk for 10 minutes.
Add eggs and meat. Pack brown sugar in bottom of a greased loaf pan.
Pour in other ingredients.
Stick cloves on top.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour and soda.
Add M&M's by hand.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: date pudding
directions: Bring to boil brown sugar and water; set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients; drop by spoonfuls into sugar mixture and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and serve upside down and topped with Cool Whip.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash and onions until tender.
Crumble cornbread and mix with other ingredients.
You may add a little water to rinse soup cans and to
moisten dressing a little more.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: beef appetizer ball
directions: Cut beef in small pieces, then mix all ingredients together, except beef.
Roll into ball and roll into (over) beef to coat the outside.
Serve with crackers.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.

title: special k loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake, covered with foil in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove foil for last 10 minutes to crisp top.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add broccoli and cook until thawed. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peach and yogurt smoothie
directions: In a blender combine peaches, vanilla, yogurt, milk, brown sugar and nutmeg.
While blending, add ice cubes through the lid, until thick and smooth.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pralines
directions: Mix everything.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Add pecans. Cook to 234°.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and let cool 5 minutes.
(Stir rapidly.)
Drop on aluminum foil.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix chicken, water chestnuts, celery and almonds.
In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, curry, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Up to 4 hours before serving, gently stir mayonnaise mixture and oranges into chicken mixture.
Serve on a bed of chilled lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cook stuffing as directed.
Spread stuffing in pan for bottom layer.
Place boneless chicken on top of stuffing.
Cook cream of chicken soup and pour evenly over chicken and stuffing.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with cracker crumbs and bake for 5 more minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple sauce cookies
directions: Beat together with beater applesauce, oil, brown sugar, sugar, vanilla, eggs, cinnamon, soda and allspice.
Add raisins, walnuts and flour.
Drop by spoonful on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into greased pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: delicious omelette
directions: Mix all ingredients the day before serving.
Refrigerate, then set at room temperature for one hour before baking.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves about ten.

title: fruit cake (light)
directions: Mix fruit and nuts together.
(Do not chop.)
Beat yolks and whites separately.
Add vanilla to yolks.
Pour yolks over the nut mixture slowly.
Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Add dry ingredients and beaten whites to fruit and nut mixture.
Put in oven at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not preheat oven before putting cake in.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Combine powdered sugar and cocoa.
Add margarine and mix and then add milk to desired texture.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in a little margarine or butter.
Add soup and milk; stir.
Simmer a few minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes good side dish by omitting chicken.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix together all cake ingredients and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; cool. Prepare frosting by mixing together cream cheese, butter or margarine, vanilla, powdered sugar and chopped nuts,
and frost cake when it is completely cool.

title: party deviled eggs
directions: Split eggs lengthwise and remove yolks.
Mash well.
Set egg whites aside.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon egg yolk mixture back into egg halves.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chill before serving.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Melt chocolate bits until smooth.
Add Rice Krispies and stir until coated with chocolate.
Butter a 10-inch pie plate.
Pour mixture into pie plate and spread evenly.
(This is the crust.) Let stand at room temperature.
When ready to serve, fill with ice cream and sprinkle shredded bitter chocolate on top.

title: crock-pot delight
directions: Roll stew beef in flour.
Brown (only) slowly in small amount of oil.
Put browned beef in crock-pot.
Add celery soup and 1/2 can water.
Cook for 2 hours (or until done).
Serve over rice. Wonderful over wild or brown rice.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Place in 9-inch square dish with meaty area to outside, bones to center.
Mix together next 4 ingredients.
Stuff pocket of chops with mixture.
Cover and bake 16 minutes at High power. Rotate 1/4 turn half-way through baking time.
Rest 10 minutes.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put all other ingredients in pan in layers in order given, pouring milk over the top of the last layer.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: banana oat bread
directions: Beat butter and sugar about 1 minute until blended and free of lumps.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1 tablespoon oats. Beat until batter is smooth.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Before baking, sprinkle remaining oats on batter.
Raisins or nuts may be added.

title: grilled onion
directions: Peel onion.
Cut hole in center and place crushed beef bouillon cube in hole.
Top with oleo.
Wrap onion in foil and place on grill for 30 minutes.
Do not place onion over hot coals, but more to the side and rotate onion while cooking to bake evenly.
Serves 2.

title: chocolate chip date nut cake
directions: Combine dates, soda and boiling water; let stand until cool. Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add date mixture to this and blend.
Sift 1 1/2 cups flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 3/4 teaspoon soda and add to the date and egg mixture; blend well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch waxed paper-lined pan.
Top with 1 cup chocolate chips, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tandoori chicken
directions: Combine cumin, paprika, coriander and pepper in small saucepan.
Cook, stirring, over low heat until fragrant, 1 to 2 minutes. (Be careful not to burn.)
Transfer to bowl.
Stir in yogurt, lemon juice, ginger, garlic and salt. Add chicken, tossing to coat.
Let stand 30 minutes or cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: wedding chicken
directions: Line dish with chipped beef.
Wrap chicken with bacon and lay on chipped beef.
After mixing soups and sour cream, pour over wrapped chicken.
Cover and refrigerate over night.
Preheat oven to 275 degrees.
Bake uncovered for 3 hours.

title: chocolate chip meltaways
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 5 ingredients and beat until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients and add to margarine mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla; add chocolate chips.
Shape into small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet; cool.
Makes about 8 dozen cookies.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: In a 2 quart dish, mix soup, water, rice, paprika and pepper. place chicken on rice mixture.
Sprinkle with additional paprika and pepper.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy nutty bread
directions: Place frozen loaves of bread in Pam-sprayed regular-size bread pan; let rise about half way to top of pan. Melt butter and spread evenly over loaves. Spread brown sugar and nuts over loaves. Finish letting bread rise to top of pan. Place in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until light golden crust. Remove and cool. Enjoy.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix and pour into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack 10 minutes and turn out.

title: aunt sadie's potato salad
directions: Begin with layer of shredded cabbage.
Add layer of sliced potatoes, salt, pepper and sprinkle with celery seed.
Add onion and peppers.
Add sliced eggs and spread mayonnaise over all. Be sure to use enough to cover mixture.
This is the magical ingredient.
Now start over, ending with mayonnaise and eggs. Must be refrigerated at least 24 hours before serving.
This feeds 8 to 10.

title: school house peanut butter cookies
directions: Dissolve sugar and syrup over low heat.
Remove and add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add corn flakes.
(Warm over low heat if mixture thickens too fast.)
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Press flat with moistened hands.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients; add to potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: lentil and brown rice casserole
directions: In a heavy skillet, heat the oil and saute the onions.
Add all remaining ingredients except cheese.
Mix well and pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: italian meat pie
directions: Saute green pepper and meat together; drain.
Add water, tomato paste and spaghetti mix.
Stir well.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese on unbaked bottom pie crust.
Add meat mixture to crust and cover with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand for 5 to 7 minutes before cutting.

title: chocolate chess pie(1 pie)
directions: Mix cornmeal, cocoa and sugar.
Add melted butter. Mix thoroughly.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip (optional).

title: peanut butter kisses cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have cookie sheets ready.
With wooden spoon, stir peanut butter, sugar and eggs together in bowl (dough will be slightly sticky).
With floured hands, roll mixture into balls (walnut size).
Place 1 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes, until cookies look dry and are cracked.
Remove from oven and press unwrapped kiss in the center of each cookie.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Melt butter and add soup and half and half creamer. Cook over low heat.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients with fork; mix thoroughly.
Shape into loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Combine Rice Krispies, cracker crumbs and seasoning.
Dip chicken pieces into melted butter, then dip into crumbs.
Arrange chicken in a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: hot rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine ingredients in bowl.
Batter will be thin.
Spoon into lightly greased muffin pans.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil raisins in 3/4 cup of water for 5 minutes.
Drain and cool; set liquid aside.
Mix margarine, eggs and sugar.
Stir into a cream.
Add salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix baking soda and liquid from cooked raisins and add to mixture.
Add flour, oatmeal and nuts.
Put raisins in last.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs in small pieces.
Add to other ingredients in large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Cook until the juice is almost completely absorbed.

title: lighter artichoke dip(lo-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In ovenproof dish, combine artichokes, chilies, mayonnaise and all but 2 tablespoons cheese.
Mix well. Sprinkle
remaining cheese on top and bake about 50 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Makes 3 cups.

title: roast pork loin
directions: Marinate pork loin for 1 hour in splash of orange juice, Balsamic vinegar, oil.
Heat cast iron pan, sear all sides lightly. Bake at highest heat for 30 minutes.
Remove, check with meat thermometer for 150°.
Cover for 5 minutes.

title: fruit squares
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg yolk and milk; mix well.
Take 1/2 of the dough and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with the fruit.
Dot fruit with a little butter.
Roll out the other 1/2 of dough and lay it on top of the fruit.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Cool and ice with powdered sugar and water icing.

title: cold chicken balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Roll in coconut.
Freezes very well.

title: cranberries for the holidays
directions: Wash cranberries, then add cranberries, sugar and wine.
Bring to a boil, approximately 7 minutes, until skins pop.
Then add water and cornstarch (combined and stirred into mixture).
Serve warm.
Excellent!

title: red deviled eggs
directions: Add the sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper to the beet juice.

title: cheddar potatoes
directions: Coat all potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg dish
directions: Blend first 8 ingredients; add chilies and mushrooms.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° in a 9 X 13 pan.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Mix the sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in the milk and banana.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in the nuts.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for about 70 minutes.
Cool and slice.
Serve with butter or cream cheese.

title: amish coconut pecan candy
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix thoroughly with electric mixer.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Turn out of pan and cut into 1-inch squares.
Dip into melted chocolate.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Add 1 cup water to raisins and boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Do not drain.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, nuts and raisins. Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: orange date bread
directions: Combine dates, orange peel, juice and hot water.
Stir in sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and potato granules.
Add nuts.
Bake in 9 x 5-inch pan at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: baptist church plum jam
directions: Add 1/2 cup water to plums and boil 10 minutes.
Run mixture through sieve to remove seeds.
Measure exactly 6 cups plums to 8 cups sugar.
Bring to hard boil, one that can't be stirred down. Reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir 1 box Sure-Jell. Bring back to full boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; skim off foam.
Fill jars.
Makes approximately 10 cups.

title: instant cheesecake
directions: Mix the softened cream cheese with thawed Cool Whip until creamy.
Pour in the pie shell.
Cool for 1 hour.
Top with cherry pie filling, if desired.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the first 4 ingredients in a large bowl in order listed. Spread mayonnaise over vegetables.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Top with cheese.
Chill overnight.
Yields 10 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients; mix at medium speed on an electric mixer until well blended.
Serve with fresh fruit (strawberries, grapes and apples are my favorite).

title: bread pudding
directions: Break up bread in cake pan and let dry.
Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and milk.
Pour over bread and smash down.
Use enough milk to cover bread well.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top. Stir after 20 minutes once or twice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas bark
directions: Melt coating; stir 1/3 cup peppermint pieces into it.
Pour onto wax paper and spread 1/4 to 1/8-inch thin.
Sprinkle additional peppermint pieces on top before coating sets.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together. Divide and spread on the 5 tortillas. Roll up tortillas. Cover tightly with plastic wrap. Twist ends and refrigerate several hours. Unwrap and cut 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick. Enjoy.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Put a top crust over, crimp edges and make several steam vents.
Sprinkle a little sugar over the top crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Good eating both warm and cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together; pour into a 15 x 9 x 2-inch pan greased with oleo.
Mix together 3 cups corn flake crumbs and 1/4 cup oleo. Sprinkle on top; bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Serve with a salad.

title: mayhaw jelly
directions: Combine berries and water; bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Strain through cloth bag, squeezing out juice to equal 4 cups.
Mix Sure-Jell with juice in 6 to 8-quart saucepan.
Bring quickly to a hard boil, stirring occasionally. Add sugar all at once.
Cook and stir.
When mixture returns to a full, rolling boil, cook and stir 1 minute more.
Remove from heat; skim off foam.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: 5-bean chili
directions: Saute onions in oil over medium-high heat.
Cook until onion is transluscent.
Add ground beef and garlic.
Brown and drain (do not scorch garlic).
Stir in remaining dry ingredients, except beans. Hand-crush tomatoes and add juice and all to mixture.
Add beans and beer.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Taste and adjust seasonings if desired (more cayenne and hot red pepper flakes for hotter chili).

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with your favorite seasonings.
Bake at 375° until almost done.
Place onion and bell pepper over pork chops. Mix soup and milk together well; pour over pork chops and continue to bake until chops are done, about 30 minutes.

title: dip ala somerset county
directions: You will need a knife and can opener.

title: five layer potato casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan layer the following:
sliced onions, lean ground beef, browned, sliced potatoes, frozen or canned corn and cream of mushroom soup combined with 1 soup can of water.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Place chicken, seasoning, onion and celery in kettle.
Add water; bring to boil and skim.
Then cook over medium-high heat until tender.
When cool enough, remove skin and bones.
Reserve the good skin for later.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugars, milk and salt together in large saucepan.
Bring slowly to a boil to prevent scorching (about 20 minutes); allow to boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Mix quickly, as candy hardens fast.
Turn into well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Allow to set.
Cut into squares.

title: smoked turkey casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain broccoli well; arranged in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with smoked turkey.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, soup and curry powder; pour over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and herb stuffing; drizzle butter over all.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: asparagus pasta salad
directions: Steam asparagus 4 to 6 minutes.
Cool, drain and reserve. Cook pasta; drain, rinse and drain.
Cool.

title: dessert pancakes
directions: Put ingredients in either a blender or mixer to mix well. Pour batter onto heated griddle or skillet.
When batter is full of bubbles, turn pancakes over to finish cooking.
(If you do not have self-rising flour, you may use all-purpose flour and add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon baking powder).

title: candied carrots
directions: Combine margarine, cranberry sauce, sugar and salt in skillet. Heat until cranberry sauce melts.
Add carrots, mix, glazing with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon rhubarb cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl of mixer, beat margarine and 1 1/2 cups sugar until creamed.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternating with butter and milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in rhubarb and nuts.
Spread smooth in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle on batter.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: blueberry cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Fold in berries and pecans.
Pour into 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Don't overcook.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice onion and zucchini thin. Saute both in 1 tablespoon oil for 5 to 10 minutes. Add tomatoes and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle with ground pepper and cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese has melted.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: shake and make ice cream
directions: You will also need 1 pint sized plastic zip bag and 1 gallon sized zip bag.

title: chicken dorito casserole
directions: In sauce pan, combine chicken, soups, Rotel, chili powder, onion and 1 cup lightly crushed Doritos.
Cook on stove until warm, about 10 minutes.
Cover the bottom of a 9-1/2x11-inch casserole dish with Doritos.
Lightly crush until flat.
Spread a layer of the soup mixture.
Top with a layer of Doritos.
Continue with layers, alternating, until gone.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix stick butter, eggs, pudding mix, cake mix, food coloring and water together. Beat for 3 minutes. Mix baking soda & vinegar and fold into batter. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Cook onion in margarine until tender. Beat together cream, eggs, bouillon and nutmeg. Toss cheese and flour.
Add to egg mixture along with remaining ingredients, except hard-cooked egg.
Turn in prepared shell. Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with hard-cooked egg and parsley (optional). Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix together cake mix as directed on package. Place 3/4 of the mix (or entire mix) in baking pan and bake according to package directions. Cool cake.

title: southern sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes under running water. Cook, covered in lightly salted boiling water just till tender, about 35 min. Drain, when cool enough to handle, peel and place in large bowl. While potatoes are still warm, mash with electric mixer or masher. Add butter, bourbon, orange juice, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Beat until mixture is smooth and fluffy. Preheat oven to 350°. Turn sweet potato mixture into a 2 quart casserole dish that has been lightly buttered, or using a nonstick spray, buttered flavored. pulling into attractive swirls with back of spoon. At this point may be covered and chill until ready to bake. Sprinkle nuts around edge to make border. Bake for 45 min.

title: pecan roll
directions: Melt silver bells and butter.
Take off the stove; add pecans. Let cool and add marshmallows.
Pour on foil and roll as big as a rolling pin.
Let cool for 5 or 6 hours before slicing.

title: spicy black-eyed pea soup
directions: In
a
saucepan, saute the bacon until lightly browned. Saute onions, jalapenos, tomatoes, garlic, salt and pepper in the bacon and bacon drippings.

title: shrimp and crabmeat dip
directions: Top with 2 large packages Mozzarella cheese and 1 can (large) black pitted black olives.

title: chocolate oatmeal clusters
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a pot and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and boil for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: crab cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine egg, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, lemon juice, mayonnaise, melted butter, salt and pepper. Add bread cubes.
Gently mix in crabmeat; try to avoid breaking the lumps.
Form into patties and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown.

title: pink stuff
directions: Stir together all ingredients.	Chill for 4 hours.
You may use lemon
pie
filling,
which
of
course,
makes Yellow Stuff. You may also put in a graham cracker crust.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix cornmeal and milk.
Let stand 30 minutes. Fry onion in oil until brown.
Add meat and cook until light colored.
Add tomatoes and corn. Cook 15 minutes.
Add cornmeal mixture and olives. Pour into greased casserole pan and bake 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: With a pastry blender, cut shortening into flour.
Add buttermilk and mix.
On a lightly floured board, knead for a few seconds, adding additional flour if necessary.
Roll out onto a lightly floured board into a 1/2 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread sausage over dough.
Roll up, jelly-roll style, starting from the short side.
Chill; cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Place, cut side down, on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields about 9 servings.

title: date pudding
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add remaining ingredients to the eggs. Stir and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased glass pan.
Bake at 225°.
Increase heat until up to 325°.
Slowly increase heat over a total of one hour baking time.
It will be golden brown on top when done.

title: linda's red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco, cake flour, cocoa and salt.
Blend well. Add 2/3 cup buttermilk, food coloring, eggs, vanilla, water and 1/3 cup more buttermilk.
Beat well.
Stir in by hand, vinegar and soda.
Bake in 2 layer pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix right in a 13 x 9-inch pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Check at 20 minutes with toothpick.

title: beet relish with cabbage
directions: Chop beets and cabbage very fine.
Add sugar, salt, vinegar, horseradish and pepper.
Mix cold and seal tightly.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Add 3 tablespoons butter, salt and orange juice to sweet potatoes.
Beat until light.
Fold in pineapple.
Spoon potato mixture into a 1-quart casserole.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter. Put marshmallows on top.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until marshmallows are puffed and browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hash brown potatoes casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese. Stir well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook meat until tender.
Add potatoes, onions, carrots and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce and cook in large pot.
Makes about a gallon.
Cook about 30 minutes all together.

title: huntington chicken
directions: Stew chicken and season to taste. Cook macaroni in saltwater and drain. Thicken chicken broth with flour. Mix chicken, macaroni, cheese and broth together and put in greased 9 x 13 casserole. Brown crumbs in butter; add cream and mix. Spread on top. Brown in 325° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 12 to 15.

title: hobo bread
directions: Soak the first 4 ingredients overnight or at least 4 or 5 hours.
Add sugar.
Add remaining ingredietns.
Grease and flour 3 (1 pound) coffee cans and fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: irish pork stuffing
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Fry celery and onion in pork sausage grease.
Mash the potatoes (lumpy) and add bread crumbs, celery, onion and sausage; mix well.
Place in Corning dish.
Press stuffing mixture in baking dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs on top.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken with skin and debone.
Lay chicken breasts in baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour on top of breasts.
Bake 1/2 hour to 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.
Remove from oven; top with 1 can Durkee onions.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: broccoli and mushroom salad
directions: Chop broccoli and scallions, including green tops.
Slice mushrooms.
Combine dressing and pour over vegetables.
Marinate all day in refrigerator.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on package.
Add extracts.
In two 8-inch pans, spread melted margarine.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Spread orange marmalade over this.
Pour cake mix on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: honey baked beans
directions: Fold ingredients together in a large bowl.
Transfer to a square baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven or to desired consistency.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place	in
unbaked pie shell and cook at 400° to 425° until filling is set.

title: ham and potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray large nonstick skillet and saute onions over medium heat 2 minutes.
Add green peppers, chicken broth, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes. In bowl, stir ham, corn and onion mixture.
Cover with mashed potatoes.
Roughen surface with fork.
Bake 30 minutes until flaked with brown.

title: carrot cake with buttermilk glaze
directions: Sift
together	flour,	baking soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Beat
eggs	in
bowl until lemon-colored.
Beat in sugar, oil,
buttermilk
and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture. Stir in pineapple, carrots, nuts and coconut.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Mix Bisquick and water until soft dough forms; beat 20 strokes. Pat in pan with floured hands, pressing 1/2 inch up sides.
Cook and stir ground beef until brown; drain.
Layer beef, tomatoes and green pepper on dough.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spoon over top.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Bake until edges are light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: big fat cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare mix as directed on package except use 1/2 cup of water and the eggs.
Omit oil.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: jalapeno rice
directions: Fry, but do not brown, the rice in oil.
Add onions and saute. Add peppers and grated cheese together with water and cubes.
Cut up the margarine over mixture; simmer for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: zucchini sauce for noodles
directions: Heat butter in skillet.
Add chopped mushrooms and garlic. Cook for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add zucchini and tomato sauce; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: maple sticky buns
directions: Add sugar, salt and margarine to hot potatoes; set aside.
Add yeast and eggs to make warm water.
Add flour and knead.
Let rise in greased bowl.
Punch down; chill.
Grease baking pan.
Add maple syrup and nuts.
Roll dough 1/2 inch thick.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up and cut into 1/2-inch circles.
Place in pan of syrup and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Tear bread into pieces and put into a large, greased baking dish.
Fry sausage and drain.
If using links, cut in slices.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle on grated cheese.

title: quick tarts
directions: Place biscuits on a cookie sheet.
Shape each biscuit with hand to form 4-inch tart shell.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on biscuits.
Place a spoonful of cherry pie filling on each tart.
Top with coconut or chopped nuts.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: supreme pasta salad
directions: Combine cooked pasta, Italian dressing and Salad Supreme in a large bowl and toss with remaining ingredients.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine whole and creamed corn, sour cream and Jiffy mix.
Melt butter and fold into mixture.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until top is brown.
If pudding is not set at this time, it will set after being removed from the oven.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream together margarine, sugars, vanilla and eggs. Add flour, baking soda and powder, salt, nutmeg and cloves. Gradually add zucchini, nuts and chips. Mix well. Pour into floured 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Frost and serve.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan.
Stir	in
stuffing and mix well.
Spread stuffing mixture on top of
chicken which has been mixed with soup, celery,
mayonnaise.
Assemble
casserole on morning it is to be used and refrigerate.
Bake
minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: moon cake
directions: Mix water and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Add flour all at once and stir rapidly until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Spread on ungreased 11 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: chewy cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften butter.
In large mixing bowl stir all ingredients together.
Then spread mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to mixture; alternate with buttermilk (beginning and ending with flour mixture).
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix filling ingredients together until smooth and blended well.
Spread filling over warmed up tortillas (easier to roll up if warm).
Roll up tortilla.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Uncover and cut ends off and discard.
Cut into 1/2 to 3/4-inch slices.
Lay flat on serving plate.
Makes 50 to 60 pinwheels.

title: blueberry-bran pancakes(low-fat)
directions: Crush cereal.
Mix eggs, milk, oil and cereal.
Let stand 7 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients, except berries.
Beat until smooth. Fold in berries.
Pour batter by 1/4 cup onto hot griddle. Cook pancakes until puffed and full of bubbles.
Turn. Cook until golden brown.
Makes about ten 5-inch cakes.

title: easy minestrone soup
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, brown beef with onion; drain fat.
Add tomatoes, cover and simmer 50 to 60 minutes.
Add beef broth, beans and macaroni; stir gently to combine.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Ladle into bowls and top with cheese.
Serves 6.

title: marinade vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate 24 hours.

title: corned beef noodles casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water until tender; drain.
Mix all the other ingredients, except bread crumbs into noodles.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs, cook 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine the graham cracker crumbs, margarine and granulated sugar.
Pat into the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Next, combine the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
It should be soft, so that it can easily be spread over the baked graham cracker crust.
Spread a layer of chopped nuts over the cream cheese mixture.
Add the cherry pie filling as the next layer.
Cover with whipped topping and use maraschino cherries to garnish each serving.
Serve chilled.

title: microwave quiche
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in a 9-inch Pyrex pie pan.
Beat eggs and evaporated milk until well blended.
Add seasonings. Pour over first mixture in pie pan.
Bake for 9 1/2 to 11 minutes on Medium-high with 80% power.
Cover with wax paper; let stand 5 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: hanky-panky's
directions: Cook sausage and ground beef.
Drain well.
Add oregano and garlic salt.
Melt cheese in microwave and mix with meat mixture. Spread on cocktail bread and freeze on cookie sheets.
Store in Ziplock bags until ready to serve.
Cook frozen at 400°.
Serve warm.

title: frosted salad
directions: * Grape jello with blueberry pie filling.
*Cherry jello with cherry pie filling.
*Strawberry jello with whole cranberry sauce.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and eggs together.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Grease the baking sheet.)

title: cheesy potato hot dog casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions to soften.
Add Cheddar cheese soup mixed with 1/2 can water.
Cook potato slices.
Drain. Put potatoes in casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put cheese mixture with potatoes.
Slice hot dogs and lay on top of potatoes and cheese mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Mix water and soup together.
Brown pork chops in skillet. Layer rice, soup and then pork chops in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover with foil.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian sub sandwich
directions: Pan-fry steak in 1 teaspoon oil.
Salt and pepper to taste. Saute onion and pepper until crisp-tender.
Place on a sub roll and pour desired amount of dressing.
Top with lettuce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add oil, vanilla, sugar and zucchini.
Combine flour and cinnamon together.
Mix well with egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake a 325° for 1 hour.

title: seafood dip
directions: Break shrimp and crab meat up with a fork in a bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in pecans.
Pour oleo into 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread mixture over oleo.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in maple syrup.
Beat in flour and baking soda.
Divide dough into 5 parts and roll into logs the roundness of a quarter.
Place 2 logs on an ungreased cookie sheet (need 3 cookie sheets).
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Logs will spread.
Take out and immediately cut diagonally into 1-inch strips.
Store in a tight tin.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oleo, eggs and sugar. Add crushed bananas. Sift the dry ingredients. Mix with first part and add nuts and vanilla. Pour into two loaf pans, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peggy's potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in water until half done; drain. Pour broth over potatoes and onion; cook until done.
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Add cream to soup until desired taste is achieved.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix together and let kids blow tons of bubbles.
Generic soap works great.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Peel and cut tomatoes.
Add celery, pepper, hot sauce, sugar and salt.
Cook until celery and pepper are tender.

title: pizza pockets
directions: Take both slices of bread and cover with sauce.
Spread out pepperoni on one slice and add cheese.
Put the slices of bread together.
Stick them in the oven at 375° and cook for 5 minutes, or just go to Sam's and buy them!

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in oven-safe dish.
Add fruit.
Mix flour and milk; add to fruit.
Pour in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: krab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: graham gems
directions: Mix just until moistened. Fill 12 greased muffin cups half full. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lynne's jambalaya
directions: Saute in oil the onions, bell pepper, celery and garlic.
Add sliced sausage, fresh shrimp or diced raw chicken and the remaining ingredients; simmer until rice and chicken are cooked.

title: ho-ho beans
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
May add sausages, wieners or ground beef for a heartier dish.

title: christmas morning rolls
directions: Heat together butter, brown sugar and cinnamon until sugar dissolves and mixture bubbles.
Arrange frozen rolls in a well-greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle pudding mix over rolls. Sprinkle nuts over pudding mix.
Pour butter, sugar and cinnamon mixture (while hot) over rolls and pudding.
Cover tightly with foil and let stand on counter until morning.

title: peach crumble pie
directions: Blend 1/2 cup
sugar,
cornstarch, salt, water and corn syrup. Blend well.
Add
to
peaches.
Bring to boil.
Cook 1 minute. Cool.
Add	1
tablespoon
lemon
juice.
Pour
into pastry shell. Sift together sugar and flour;
cut in oleo and lemon rind for topping.
Sprinkle	over top of pie.
Bake in a 425° oven 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy chicken
directions: Brown chicken.
Place in an oblong pan.
Add soups, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes its own gravy.

title: bonbon candy
directions: Form chilled mixture into small balls.
Dip in melted chocolate and place on waxed paper to harden.
Makes 100 pieces.

title: fruit salad with pudding(serves 8)
directions: Combine all fruit in bowl.
In separate bowl, mix milk (or yogurt) with pudding.
Layer in casserole dish, beginning with fruit and ending with pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: barbecued short ribs
directions: Heat a large skillet over medium high heat and brown the short ribs on all sides.
Place the ribs in a slow cooker and top with the onions.
In a medium bowl, combine the water, beef granules, barbecue sauce, brown sugar and Dijon mustard.
Pour sauce over ribs, cover and cook on low for about 6-7 hours, or until tender.
Add the cornstarch mixture and continue to cook until the sauce thickens, about 20 minutes.

title: homemade cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Fry hamburger until brown and drain fat.
Add the soup and cook on medium-low for about 10 minutes.
Pour hamburger into a deep-dish pie pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle corn evenly over the meat.
Spoon heaping tablespoonfuls of mashed potatoes over the corn and then carefully smooth out the mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then sprinkle Cheddar cheese over the potatoes and bake until it melts.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place into 9-inch pie plate, then put into refrigerator, covered with foil, for about 15 or 20 minutes until hardened.

title: black bean and corn relish
directions: In a large bowl, combine beans, corn, cilantro, onions and red bell peppers.
Add Italian dressing, salt and pepper and gently mix to blend well.
Refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Taste and adjust seasoning with salt, black pepper and dressing.

title: applesauce cinnamon raisin bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, adding yeast last.
Cover and let rise 2 hours.
Punch down, place in greased loaf pan and let rise another 2 hours.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Remove from pan and let cook on rack.

title: easy baked italian chicken
directions: First, buy a microwave oven.

Then take out two tea cups (or you could use a bowl or small glass pitcher, if you have one). However, it may be best not to clutter the kitchen with cooking utensils lest somebody thinks you should use them!

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 2 cups water for 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Mix mushroom soup and cheese until melted.
Pour over broccoli mix. Place broccoli mixture in greased baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: super sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned; drain well. Stir in the next 7 ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Spoon ground beef mixture on bottom half of buns and cover with bun tops.

title: old fashioned soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat.
Add milk, vanilla, flour, baking powder and soda.
Mix well.
Drop on sheet.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes or until golden.

title: dill dressing
directions: Let soak 30 minutes together.
This is good with cabbage, carrot and onion slaw.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Boil to soft-ball stage.
Beat in 1 1/2 cups pecan halves. Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and pour out on buttered waxed paper.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Heat chicken stock.
Add celery and carrots.
Cook until vegetables are tender; set aside.
Heat butter in saucepan.
Add onion and saute lightly.
Add flour and stir with a wire whip; cook 2 to 4 minutes, making sure flour and butter are well blended.
Add vegetable broth and milk; stir with wire whip and bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low as it thickens.
Add cheese and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Garnish with fresh chopped parsley or bacon bits.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar together.
Cream sugar, lard and eggs.
Mix into flour mixture.
Add vanilla and raisins or nuts.
Make in rolls the night before.
Slice in the morning. Leave plenty of room to spread.
Bake at 350°.

title: special chicken salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve on bed of lettuce with a slice of cantaloupe.
Quick and easy.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease baking dish.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pare and thinly slice apples into baking dish.
Cut shortening into sugar and flour/crumb mixture.
Spread sugar mixture over apples.
Cinnamon may be sprinkled over apples or mixed into topping.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with ice cream, whipped cream or plain.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy hot fudge
directions: Heat and blend in double boiler or in microwave.
If too thick, add hot water.

title: bologna or ham spread
directions: Grind or chop meat, green pepper and onion.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: prairie fire dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except the corn chips in a saucepan. Cook over low heat until cheese is melted and dip is heated through.
Serve warm with corn chips.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: arizona meat and beans in crock-pot
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Brown salt pork in large skillet. Remove with slotted spoon to cooker.
Saute onions, garlic and green pepper.
In pan drippings, brown beef a few pieces at a time. Remove with slotted spoon to cooker.
Add salt, oregano, red pepper, cumin and tomato sauce to cooker.
Stir.
Add more water if necessary to bring liquid level above beans.
Cover.
Cook on low 190° to 200° for 10 hours.	Or cook on high 290° or 300° for 6 hours or until beans are tender.

title: best rice
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour into a large casserole dish with tight-fitting lid.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: acapulco fiesta salad
directions: Combine sour cream, seasonings and vinegar for dressing.

title: cocoa-apple cake
directions: Beat together first four ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and apples. Spoon into greased and floured tube or loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook chicken in water with bay leaf until tender.
Discard skin and bones.
Cut meat into 1-inch pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients with chicken, except cheese and onion rings.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole 20 minutes. Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Top with onion rings and bake 2 minutes longer.
Serves 10.

title: broccoli chicken bake
directions: Cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with chopped broccoli.
Dot with butter.
Cover with grated cheese; top with diced chicken.

title: frosting cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients with mixer.
Add the frosting; mix well.
Add the chopped pecans; mix well.
Spray and flour a Bundt pan.
Pour mixture in.
Bake on top rack of oven at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan while hot.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, cook onions in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients; simmer for 5 minutes.

title: salmon or tuna chowder
directions: Prepare salmon by removing skin and bones and breaking into chunks.
Cook potatoes and carrots in broth until tender.
Saute onion and celery in oil until tender.

title: hidden valley boursin cheese spread
directions: Beat all ingredients together, using electric mixer or processor.
Spoon into 3 cup bowl or crock; cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before serving.
Keeps great!

title: foxglove pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add sour cream and lemon juice and mix until smooth.
Cook all ingredients, except yolks, until thick, stirring constantly.
Add yolks and cook 1 minute more. Pour into prebaked 10-inch deep pie shell.
Cover and cool.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Make a pocket in the breast and insert some garlic and a pat of butter.
Dip in egg and then roll in bread crumbs.
Place in well-buttered baking dish and put additional butter on each breast.
(Can be melted on pats of butter.) Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until tender and brown.
Serve with rice and green vegetable.

title: cheese log
directions: Soften cream cheese in top of double boiler.
Add garlic powder.
Will be messy at first.
Make rolls.
Roll in chili powder, mixed with paprika.
Can be frozen.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Combine the juice, pecans, vanilla, pineapple with juice, cranberries, dates and eggs.
Sift the flour, cinnamon, baking soda and allspice; add to fruit mixture and stir well.
Spoon batter into 6-cup Bundt pan or 6 1/2-inch tube pan that has been coated with cooking oil or spray.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in cake comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan 20 minutes.
Remove and cool completely on wire rack.
Wrap in foil and let set on counter 2 days.
Store in refrigerator.
This also freezes well.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together and bake in tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: rotini pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until tender; drain and rinse in cold water.
Mix both envelopes of dressing as directed on package.
Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Stir well and chill overnight in fridge. You can add pepperoni or salami.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: Mix macaroni together with remaining ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: salami
directions: Mix together and make a roll 12-inches long. Wrap in aluminum foil with shiny side in. Refrigerate 21 hours. Poke holes in bottom of foil (underneath side). Place on rack of broiler pan with 1/2 to 1-inch of water in bottom of pan. Water should not touch foil. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: baked french toast
directions: In a large flat dish, combine the eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Let the bread soak in the mixture in one layer for 2 minutes, turn it, and let it soak until it has been absorbed.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix together and it's ready to serve or keep in refrigerator. The longer it sets, the better!

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In one pot, cook stew beef, carrots, onion, salt and pepper and bouillon cube. I pressure cook this, but can be cooked 1 to 2 hours slowly until very tender in a large pot over low heat on regular burner. In another pot, cook tomatoes, corn, butter beans, sugar, string beans and potatoes until tender, then add tomato soup. Put all together in one pot. Stir well. Put cheese in bottom of bowl, soup on top and serve with crackers. Stir often; do not allow to stick. Be sure there is enough water.

title: pineapple fritters
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan or deep fryer to 350°.
Combine milk, sugar, egg, cinnamon, vanilla, nutmeg and salt in medium bowl and beat well.
Stir in pineapple with reserved juice.
Sift in flour and baking powder and stir just until dry ingredients are evenly moistened.
Drop batter into hot oil in batches by rounded tablespoons.
Fry until deep golden, about 3 minutes per side. Drain on paper towel.
Serve immediately.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Serve with raw veggies, pretzels or tasty crackers.

title: citrus nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, thoroughly stir together flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Combine egg, orange peel and juice, lemon peel and juice and cooking oil.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in nuts. Turn batter into greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.
Wrap in foil and store overnight before slicing. Makes 1 loaf.

title: apricot lace cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir well.
Add margarine, flavoring and eggs, mix well.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto cookie sheets coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Let stand 2 minutes, loosening edges gently from sheet.
Place on racks.
Cool completely.
Spread 1/2 teaspoon of fruit spread on bottoms of half of cookies; top with remaining cookies.
Place chocolate in a heavy-duty Ziploc bag.
Place in hot water until chocolate melts. Snip a tiny hole in bottom corner of bag.
Drizzle chocolate over cookies.
Yields about 3 dozen double cookies.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cut sausage into bite-size pieces and cook 5 to 6 minutes over low heat.
Add onion and green pepper; saute until tender.
Add beans, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: oven stew
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in large bowl or Dutch oven. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 4 hours at 275°.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries, apple and orange through a food processor. Add sugar and mix well.
Store chilled until ready to use.

title: ranch pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; boil for 5 minutes.
Pour into an 8-inch square dish. Mix the remaining ingredients.
Spoon batter on top of sugar mixture.
It will sink into the liquid and spread out as it bakes. Bake for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with plain or whipped cream.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick of oleo. Press into bottom of a 9 x 12 pan. Combine confectioners sugar, eggs and 2 sticks of oleo. Whip for 15 minutes. Spread this mixture over the crumbs. Slice bananas over this. Drain pineapple and spread over bananas. Spread Cool Whip over pineapple. Cut cherries in half and layer over the Cool Whip. Sprinkle with pecans. Refrigerate overnight.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cuban black beans
directions: Use slow cooker on low, all day, for best results.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion, celery and garlic. Cook until tender.
Add flour, salt, sugar, cayenne pepper, paprika, bay leaf and liquid hot pepper sauce.
Stir until blended and smooth.
Add green pepper, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook 20 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add fresh shrimp and cook 10 minutes or until shrimp are pink.
Serve on rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: cajun catfish
directions: Sprinkle
dressed
catfish
with Creole seasoning.
Dot with margarine.	Cover
with foil and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Very spicy!

title: marinated zucchini
directions: Trin ends of the zucchini and slice lengthwise.
Sprinkle with salt and arrange the slices on a plate positioned at a slight angle, so that the zucchini will lose some of its moisture.
Let drain for a few hours, then dry with kitchen towel.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Arrange potato wedges in shallow baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Spoon sauce over potatoes several times during cooking.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread rice on bottom.
Mix both cans of soup and 1 can of water.
Spread half of this mixture over rice.
Stir with a fork to moisten.
Salt and pepper chicken and place on top of rice.
Dot with butter.
Spread remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle dry soup on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt the butterscotch chips, peanut butter chips, chocolate bars and wax or Crisco over medium heat.
When melted, remove from heat and add can of peanuts.
Drop on wax paper and let harden.

title: uncooked cookies or no bakes
directions: Bring to a boil all ingredients, except oats. Boil for 3 minutes, then pour uncooked quick oats in cooked mixture.
Stir until it cools a little.
Then drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Sprinkle dry pudding over pineapple and juice.
Stir until dissolved.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and chill before serving.

title: blooming good pudding
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients and bring to a boil. Do not boil. Set aside to cool. When cool make the
remainder of the recipe.

title: orange cake
directions: Grind first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar in large bowl.
Add 1/4 cup milk to dry ingredients; add eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining 1/4 cup milk.
Fold in ground mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 to 50 minutes in oblong pan.

title: sugarless banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop raisins into boiling water to reduce stickiness.
Mash bananas and stir in remaining ingredients.
Place spoon size mounds on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes.
Can be served warm or cooled.

title: cocoa-peanut butter mounds
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Add butter and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: tropical cream punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine milk and juices.
Mix well.
Gradually add club soda.
Stir.
Garnish with orange slices and serve over ice.

title: crabmeat puffs
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in mayonnaise and crab. Season to taste and put on bread rounds.
Broil for about 3 minutes until puffy and brown.
Serve immediately.

title: savory baked chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Put egg whites in pie pan and beat slightly.
Combine remaining ingredients in another pie pan.
Dip chicken into egg whites and then into dry ingredients, turning to coat.
(If coating looks dry, moisten with any remaining egg white.)
Place coated chicken into a baking pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked beans with pineapple
directions: Bake 30 minutes.
Top with pineapple chunks and bake 30 minutes more at 350°.

title: cauliflower supreme
directions: Fry bacon until brown; remove fat and add onion and pepper and cook until onion is translucent.
Add flour and blend well.
Add tomato juice and salt.
Break raw cauliflower into small flowerets.
Place all ingredients in large baking dish; cook in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Mix milk, baking powder, salt, sugar and flour together.
Stir until smooth.
Then stir in the cornmeal.
Pour into hot, greased muffin pan or cornstick pan.
Makes 6 cornmeal muffins or 7 cornsticks.
Double recipe if more is needed.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until firm, then brown.

title: mozzarella potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with peels on.
Let cool, peel, grate, then add remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Remove crust and slice each slice into 3 strips. Spread mixture on each strip of bread. Then roll up, then wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around each and secure with a toothpick. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Place pineapple in bottom of baking dish. Mix sugar and flour together. Sprinkle over pineapple. Add cheese and crackers. Pour melted butter over top. Bake at 350 for 30 min.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in the top of a double boiler.
Stir until smooth and blended.
Pour fudge into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: ham and macaroni toss
directions: Chop vegetables.
Combine soup, celery, onion, green pepper, mustard, Tabasco sauce and pepper.
Add macaroni and ham.
Chill. Serve with tomato wedges.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix all of these ingredients together and shake well. Make 2 hours ahead of time. Clean and de-stem 1 bag of spinach. Clean and hull fresh strawberries then slice thin. To a large glass bowl, layer spinach, strawberries, and pecans or silvered almonds. Add dressing when ready to serve.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Kool Aid and water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Freeze overnight.
Remove several hours before serving. Serve slushy.
Makes 20 to 30 cups.

title: lemon-orange concentrate
directions: Grate rinds and squeeze juice from lemons and oranges.
Strain juices if desired.
Add boiling water to sugar and citric acid. Cool.
Mix syrup and juices.
Bottle and refrigerate.
One cup of concentrate makes 2 quarts of drink.

title: raisin sauce(for ham)
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together in saucepan.
Add salt, water and butter.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add beer, raisins and mustard and cook until raisins are plump and mixture begins to boil.
Great with canned ham.

title: heavenly carrots
directions: Place carrots in buttered casserole. Top with croutons.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Can be made to this point and refrigerated overnight.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk.
Remove from heat.
Add crackers, nuts and coconut.
Line a 9 x 11-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Put filling on top.
Cover with more crackers.
Frost with white or chocolate frosting.

title: sauerbraten hamburgers
directions: Cut tortillas into 8 pie-shaped pieces.
Pour 1/4 inch of cooking oil into a nonstick frying pan.
Fry tortillas lightly until softened, not crisp.
Drain oil.
Add a tablespoon of butter (optional).
Add eggs, lightly breaking yolks (do not beat eggs). Gently fold mixture over several times until eggs are cooked through and mixed well with the tortilla sections.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with sour cream, salsa, cilantro and chopped onions on the side.
Serves 2 as a complete meal or more if other foods, such as vegetables, etc., are served.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Soak in 4 beaten eggs for 4 hours.
Shake pieces in bread crumbs and brown in margarine. Brown chicken 1/3 at a time.
Place in large baking dish and pour chicken broth over top.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour butter into shallow 2-quart baking dish and set aside. Drain peaches, reserving 1/4 cup of juice.
In a saucepan bring peaches and juice just to a boil.
Remove from heat.
In mixing bowl combine 1 cup sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt. Mix well.
Pour over butter in baking dish.
Spoon hot peaches over butter.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: squash delight
directions: Boil cut squash in salted water five minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except the egg.
Beat the egg and pour over entire mixture.
Pour into a casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs made from 10 to 12 crackers.
I melt about 3 tablespoons margarine and pour over the cracker crumbs and then sprinkle with more grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: elaine's mexican dip
directions: Place all ingredients except chips in a small glass casserole dish.
Microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Stir until cream cheese is mixed in well.
Microwave 3 more minutes on High.
Serve hot! Serve with chips.

title: butterflake loaf
directions: Put biscuits into greased 9x5x3 pan, making two rolls.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Put crushed pineapple on stove and bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O to pineapple and stir for 3 minutes.
Let cool to room temperature, then mix in your cream cheese.
Fold in whipping cream that has been beaten stiff.
Add marshmallows and pecans.
Place in refrigerator or you can freeze this (either way it is good).

title: porcupines
directions: Shape a small portion of hamburger 1/2 x 2-inches in hand. Roll in rice.
Place in pan.
Pour in tomato soup and 3 soup cans of water.
Cover, bring to boil, then turn heat to low.
Cook about 1 hour.

title: roast rabbit
directions: Rabbits may be marinated in the game marinade for 2 to 3 days. If so, then it will not be necessary to use the wine and vinegar; use the marinade instead.
Mix salt, pepper, thyme and marjoram and rub it over the rabbits.
Lay the salt pork over the rabbits and roast, uncovered, for about 30 minutes at 450°.
Reduce the temperature to 350° and roast another hour.
Remove rabbits and add wine, vinegar (or marinade), onion and broth.
Simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add jelly, sour cream, salt and pepper to taste.
Prepare a thin paste of flour and water.
Add this to the pan and allow it to thicken.

title: overnight egg souffle casserole
directions: Cut each sausage link into 4 pieces.
Cook until brown; drain and set aside.
Combine eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Layer croutons, cheese, sausage and egg mixture in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: elaine's spinach souffle(brunch)
directions: Mix altogether and pour into 7 x 11-inch baking dish. Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grilled bologna with mustard sauce
directions: Place bologna on grill.
Mix remaining ingredients together; heat to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Baste bologna frequently with sauce.
Serve as soon as heated through and lightly brown.

title: french pudding
directions: *Sliced bananas may be substituted for the crushed pineapple.

title: spaghetti pizza bake
directions: Cook spaghetti to package directions.
Drain; add margarine and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Boil pepperoni for 5 minutes. Drain.
Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain and add spices and tomato sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
In a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, layer in order:
spaghetti, pepperoni, 2 cups Mozzarella cheese and meat mixture.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Salt and flour chicken.
Heat oil in skillet.
Brown chicken, then remove.
Add remaining ingredients.
Return chicken to the skillet and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: angel cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Add next 5 ingredients, spreading evenly over the melted butter.
Pour condensed milk over top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the butter, shortening, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and chocolate chips or nuts.
Bake for 8 minutes or until desired doneness.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until tender-crisp; drain. Arrange broccoli stalks in greased 11 x 17-inch baking dish. Place chicken slices on top.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. May be made a day ahead and refrigerated until time to bake. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spinach pie parma
directions: Combine croutons and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch pie plate.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Arrange vegetables in casserole dish (first 4 ingredients). Mix together butter, Worcestershire sauce and mushroom soup.
Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake until bubbly.
Top with Durkee's fried onions.

title: easy tamale pie
directions: Cook together butter, onions and green peppers until softened, not brown, then brown ground meat, stirring to break up. Add all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: miniature ham puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to rolling boil in 3-quart saucepan. Stir in flour. Stir vigorously until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Beat in eggs, all at once, until smooth and glossy.
Drop dough by rounded spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown, puffed and dry, about 25 minutes. Cool on wire racks. Blend ham, sour cream and salt.
Just before serving, cut off puffs with sharp knife. Fill each puff with a teaspoon of ham mixture.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen appetizers.

title: dill pickles
directions: To each quart jar of cucumbers, add dill, garlic, pickling spice and alum.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers, seal and process in water bath for 3 to 5 minutes. Enjoy!

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 350 cookies!

title: microwave taco casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion 6 minutes per pound on High in Tupperware colander in microwave.
Mix taco sauce with meat.
Stir in tortilla shells.
Layer in 1 3/4-quart Tupperware casserole, ground beef mixture, sour cream and cheeses and then add another layer of each in same order.
Microwave for nine minutes at 70% power with cover vented, turning 2 to 3 times during cooking.

title: applesauce cake(very old recipe)
directions: Mix all together and turn into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: steak diane
directions: Pound steaks to 1/3-inch thickness.
Sprinkle one side of steak with salt, freshly ground pepper and some of the dry mustard.
Pound into meat.
Repeat with other side of steak.
Melt margarine in blazer pan of chafing dish over direct heat or in skillet.
Add 2 steaks; cook 2 minutes on each side.
Place on hot serving plate.
Repeat, cooking remaining steaks.
Add remaining ingredients to blazer pan; bring to a boil.
Place steaks in chafing dish.
Spoon sauce over.
Garnish with mushrooms.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need a 10 to 12-inch plastic flowerpot and assorted silk flowers or silk plant.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add butter (melted) and small amount of buttermilk; then add beaten egg yolks.
Add remainder of buttermilk and lemon extract; add lightly beaten egg whites.
Pour into crust and bake like custard pie.

title: coconut crunch delight
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl and press into 13 X 9 inch pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes, taking out and stirring every 10 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool, then divide in 1/2. Place 1/2 back in pan to cover bottom.
Spoon pudding mixture over crumbs and top with remaining crumbs sprinkled on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a buttered dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and Ritz cracker crumbs.
Dot top with butter.
Brown for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve jello, Kool-Aid and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Pour into popsicle molds.
Makes 20 to 24 popsicles.

title: prune cake
directions: Fold in egg whites last.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 375°.

title: italian burgers
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion, soup, catsup, water and oregano.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Spread mixture on split toasted buns.
Top with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: fig jam
directions: Mix figs and sugar well; cook 20 minutes.
Add gelatin.
Mix well.
Cook 10 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; add water gradually. Cook over medium heat until smooth and thick. Stir constantly. Beat egg yolk and pour a little hot mixture over them gradually. Stir constantly.
Add to pan. Return to heat. Cook 2 minutes. Add lemon and butter. Mix well. Cool; pour into pastry shell. Top with meringue; bake.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cut salt pork into 1/2-inch pieces.
Fry pork until golden brown.
Remove pork.
Dice and fry onions in remaining pork grease.
Boil potatoes.
Cut into cubes.
Boil fish.
Remove skin and bones.
Keep 2 cups of water from boiled fish.
Combine all ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and place them in a kettle.
Add cold water and a dash of salt.
Cook until fork tender.
Drain.
Put the potatoes back in the empty pot and hold over the flame for a minute or two until the skins burst.
Peel while hot.
Chill and then chop fine.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: chocolate chunk cookie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine baking soda and salt in a bowl and set aside.
Combine butter and sugar in bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
With mixer running, slowly add corn syrup, egg and vanilla.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes or until mixed thoroughly.
Add flour mixture and beat another 2 minutes, until mixed thoroughly.
Stir in pecans and half the chocolate.

title: texas tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in seal tight container.
Use as much as taste prefers.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Mix together the margarine, 1 1/2 cups sugar, egg, vanilla and milk with electric mixer.
Add flour, soda and rhubarb.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top of batter with mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn, tomato and squash casserole
directions: Cut corn off cob; scrape well.
Dice tomatoes in large pieces. Slice squash 1/4 inch thick.
Dice green pepper and slice onion thinly in rings.
Mix well.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Melt margarine in small skillet; stir in rest of ingredients until smooth.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and baking powder; set aside.
In another bowl, beat the eggs and milk; stir in corn and margarine. Stir into dry ingredients just until blended.
In an electric skillet, heat oil to 375°.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoonfuls into hot oil; fry for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Serve with syrup.
Yield: about 2 dozen.

title: meringue jam squares
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add flour and salt and beat well.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Pat firmly into greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese cake with pineapple or lemon pudding
directions: Stir cream cheese until soft.
Blend in 1/2 milk.
Add rest of milk and preceding mix.
Beat slowly with eggbeater just until well mixed (1 minute). Pour at once into graham crust.
Sprinkle graham crumbs over top.
Chill for one hour.

title: double-up cherry salad
directions: Dissolve cherry jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in tart cherry pie filling.
Pour into 12 x 20 x 2-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let set.

title: chocolate bar (hershey) cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Pour into 3 greased 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 325° about 25 minutes or until done.
(Could be more or less than 25 minutes.)
Cool completely after removing from pans.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and granulated sugar until mixture is real creamy.
Save 2 candy bars for later.
Chop 8 or 10 candy bars very fine (I use knife instead of grater).
Fold cream cheese mixture and chopped candy into whipped toppling.
Spread between layer and on top sides.
Sprinkle remaining candy bars over cake and around sides.

title: crab swiss bites
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Separate each roll into 3 layers. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Mix all other ingredients together and spoon on top of each roll.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
May freeze before or after baking, 17 to 18 minutes. Baking time makes them crispier.

title: heath bar cookies(microwave and oven)
directions: Put whole graham crackers in bottom of 11 x 16-inch jelly roll pan.
Melt oleo.
Add sugar and nuts to oleo in glass bowl.
Heat in microwave and boil 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with chocolate (while hot).
Spread the chocolate to cover.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: tex-mex
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain and rinse off; add beans, rice and picante sauce.
In a baking dish, layer hamburger mix with a layer of cheese until all used up.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with chips and sliced jalapeno peppers.

title: unflappable chicken
directions: Note:
Need one large (14 x 20-inch) cooking bag.

title: eggplant caviar
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pierce eggplant in several places with a knife.
Bake on a cookie sheet until soft, about 50 minutes, turning midway through.
Remove from oven and cool.
Cut eggplant lengthwise
in half.
Scoop out the pulp and finely chop.
In large bowl, combine the pulp with the onion, tomato, garlic, oil and vinegar.
Mix well and season with salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Place in serving dish; garnish with parsley.
Serve with pita triangles or cocktail rye bread.

title: chocolate candy cake
directions: Bring to a boil the oil, butter, water and cocoa.
Place the sugar, flour and soda in a large bowl.
Pour the hot ingredients over the dry and beat well.
Add the buttermilk, cinnamon and eggs.
Bake in a large cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: no fat cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese up into a microwavable dish.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes. Microwave in covered dish on High for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 3 minutes more and stir.
Continue to microwave until cheese is completely melted.
Dip over low-fat nacho chips.
Store dip in refrigerator; heat up for a snack.

title: mmmmmmmm punch
directions: Soften sherbet and ice cream slightly.
Mix in pineapple juice.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Makes a delicate punch.
May substitute other sherbet and ice cream flavors to vary color and taste.
Always complimented!

title: mr. goodbar
directions: Mix until crumbly the cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Spread in an 11 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
