Mix the powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese until smooth.
Pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Leave in pan to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chili for two
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Add hamburger and cook to desired consistency over medium heat.

title: ham and cheese appetizers
directions: Mix ingredients together and spoon in the center of crescent roll.
Roll and fold each over and crimp the edges to make triangles.
Brush top with beaten egg and bake until brown at 350°.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine butter and cream cheese and mix well. Slowly add sugar and mix well.
Stir in salt and vanilla. Beating well after each addition, add eggs one at a time.
Add cake flour.
Beat well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn oven temperature to 275° and bake cake until tester inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour and 45 minutes.
It may be necessary to bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes, depending on oven.
Cool on a wire cooling rack in pan 15 to 20 minutes.

title: montgomery inn baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Combine onion and bacon in a skillet and saute until onions are transparent, then remove from stove. Combine beans, mustard, brown sugar and Ribs King barbecue sauce in large mixing bowl; mix thoroughly.
Put all of this into an ovenproof baking dish, uncovered, in oven for one hour at 350°.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer rest of ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Fill pan with cold water 1 inch over eggs.
Bring water to a rapid boil.
Set aside and cover for 25 minutes.
Cool eggs immediately.
Slice eggs in half and remove yolk.
Mash with a fork.
Add Miracle Whip, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and onion salt.
Heap into egg shell.
Sprinkle with pepper and crisscross with a fork.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix mashed figs, jello and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil; reduce to medium heat.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring often.
Quickly pour into jars and seal.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: picture perfect zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla and mix well.
Beat in zucchini until just mixed.
Set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Divide into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Loaf is done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: ravioli dough
directions: Sift flour and salt together and place on board.
Drop eggs in center.
Add butter and mix.
Add enough water to make a rather stiff dough.
Knead until smooth.
Cover; let stand 10 minutes. Divide dough; roll on lightly floured board until very thin.
Fill with cheese or meat mixture and seal.
Pinch the edges together with fingers.
Place in rapid boiling, salted water.
Cook 10 minutes.
Drain and add to spaghetti sauce.

title: dixie peanut brittle
directions: In a skillet, add sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Boil until mixture cracks when tested in cold water.
Add peanuts; boil on low heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Nuts should be light brown in color. Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Let foam up good.
Pour out on a greased cookie sheet.
When cold, break in pieces.

title: oyster fritters
directions: Mix together the pancake mix, oysters, onion, baking powder, egg, salt and pepper.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes about 20 fritters.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix all together and eat.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Pour mix over vegetables.
Let stand 24 hours.
Will keep 1 week or more.
Weight Watchers.

title: angel food pie
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, salt and water and bring to a boil. Dissolve cornstarch in the 3 tablespoons cold water and stir into boiling mixture.
Lower heat and cook and stir until cornstarch is well blended and mixture is clear.
Cool to lukewarm then fold in egg whites.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream sweetened to taste.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Turn on electric mixer at low speed.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, and mix until well blended. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Mix well. Fold in blueberries. Grease muffin tins or use cupcake papers. Fill tins about 3/4 full and sprinkle with sugar. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Let cool for 30 minutes before serving. Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: microwave meatballs
directions: Mix above ingredients; shape into balls.
Place in a single layer in baking dish.

title: noodles
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix ingredients except butter and paprika. Drizzle butter over noodles and sprinkle paprika over for "color." Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tiny meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mold into a rounded, flat loaf in a 9-inch pie plate.
Heat 15 to 17 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes to firm before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown onion, pepper and ground beef (drain).
Add to this tomatoes, Ro-Tel tomatoes, taco mix, corn and peas.
Boil egg noodles until tender.
Drain.
Place in casserole half of noodles. Put half of meat mixture over noodles.
Put layer of sliced cheese, then repeat layers.
Put in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind together smoked ham and pork shoulder.
Add crushed crackers, milk, eggs, tomato soup and pepper.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns for 30 minutes.
Melt butter or margarine. Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 13 x 9 dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: easy sticky buns(weight watchers)
directions: Spray 8-inch round pan. Pour mixture of ingredients into pan. Layer biscuits on top of mixture. Bake at 375° for 18 to 22 minutes. Makes 10 servings.

title: mavis' banana bread
directions: Mix melted margarine and mashed bananas together.
Add cake mix and eggs; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans or greased muffin pans.
Bake at 325°.
Yields 2 loaves or 18 to 20 muffins.

title: zesty french salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in an airtight jar and shake.
Chill, then shake again before serving.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Bring corn syrup to a rolling boil.
Stir peanut butter into boiling syrup.
Stir vanilla into mixture.
Pop a regular bag of popcorn.
Remove unpopped popcorn.
Stir in peanut butter mixture. Put on cookie sheet.
Eat warm or let cool and dry some.
Store in an airtight container.

title: depression era cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water for 15 minutes.
Set off and pour in 1 cup cold water, when cool add flour to coat.
Mix lard and sugar together.
Add this to floured raisins.
Sift together flour and spices and add to raisin mixture.
Bake real slow until golden brown.

title: ratatouille
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer vegetables in a large shallow pan. Add seasonings to taste.
Mix oil and water.
Sprinkle over top. Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour or until tender.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in pan.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Mix well and pour on melted butter.
Then add desired fruit.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Crust will bake to the top of cobbler.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix well and roll out on a floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into rounds.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: date walnut double decker
directions: Combine and blend to fine crumbs.
Pack into 9-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Mix ingredients (except bread crumbs) and place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs or potato chips.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth, let cool.
Add onions, green pepper and olives to rice.
Drain artichokes, saving marinade. Combine marinade, curry powder and mayonnaise until blended.
Add dressing and artichokes to salad and chill for 24 hours.
Add shrimp.

title: mashed potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, onion, parsley, lemon juice and paprika.
Spread evenly into pie crust.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Can be used as a main course with a salad or as a side dish.

title: stuffing for turkey or pork chops
directions: Saute sausage, chopped onion and celery in a large skillet. Pour water over above mixture.
If desired, boil giblets and neck of turkey and use this liquid, also.
Place bread in a large casserole dish or cake pan.
Sprinkle the bread with sage, salt and pepper.
Pour sausage mixture over the bread.
Mix well. Bake, uncovered, at 350° to the desired degree of brown.
Stir frequently.

title: festive frozen mint pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine milk, peppermint extract and food coloring.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Cover. Freeze for 6 hours or until firm.

title: garlic tomato creamies
directions: Peel and
slice tomatoes.
Cut as many tomato rounds as toast rounds.
Put
a
slice of tomato on each piece of toast. Mix mayonnaise
with
garlic. Spread on tomatoes.
Broil for 3 minutes until
brown.
Sprinkle with chives and bacon. Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread the potatoes on bottom of medium size casserole dish. Cover potatoes with cheese. Spread soup over the cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, butter and pineapple and mix well.
Add bread cubes.
Spread in 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with ham dinner.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and condensed milk.
Add lemonade, thawed and undiluted.
Mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate.
Best when refrigerated overnight before slicing.

title: strawberry and chicken salad
directions: Toss romaine in large bowl with chicken cuts, oranges, strawberries and onion. Sprinkle with almonds. Serve with dressing. Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate screwball cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Make 3 wells; in one, put oil, in one, vinegar and one, vanilla.
Pour water over all and mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade dog biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in the warm water.
Stir in warm chicken broth and molasses.
Stir in 1 cup all-purpose flour, wheat flour, cracked wheat, cornmeal, dry milk, salt and garlic powder; mix well.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface.
Knead in enough of remaining flour to make a very stiff dough (10 to 12 minutes total).
Divide dough in half; cover and let rest for 10 minutes.
On the floured surface, roll each portion to 3/8-inch thickness for large dogs or 1/4-inch thickness for small dogs. Using 2 to 4-inch cutters, cut dough into desired shapes.

title: bible cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys and girls and you will have a good cake.
Proverbs 23:14

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add ingredients and chill.

title: brandied fruit cake
directions: Mix all together very well, except the nuts and fruits.
Then fold in the nuts and fruits.
Heat the oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix everything (except potatoes) in a large mixing bowl.
Stir potatoes in last.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° until onions are done.

title: summer supper salad
directions: Boil macaroni according to package instructions.
Set aside to cool after draining.
Boil eggs, peel and cool; then chop all but 1 egg.
Boil shrimp in salted water until done, then drain and cool.
When all are cooled, mix with olives, celery, pickles and onions.
Add mayonnaise, then drained peas and toss lightly. Smooth top of salad and garnish with slices of 8th egg, extra olives and pickles.
Chill thoroughly until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers, sliced tomatoes and lettuce.

title: chicken cheese soup
directions: Boil chicken (cover with water) with celery and onion.
Add salt, pepper and garlic.
Return diced chicken to broth; add 1 quart water.
Bring to boil.
Add noodles; boil until noodles are tender.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Serves 4.

title: white chili
directions: Cover beans with water and cook until soft.
Drain and add rest of the ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 hour, until vegetables are done. May be thickened, if desired.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.
(We were given this recipe by some vegetarian friends and it may look strange, but it is great!)

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix first four ingredients, using only 4 ounces of the Cheddar cheese.
Spoon into tortilla shells and roll.
Lay rolled shells in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon over tortilla shells.
Top with remaining half of Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Place bananas (sliced) on bottom of pie crust.
Then add the ice cream, then hot fudge, pineapple, hot fudge and then Cool Whip. Add pecans and decorate with cherries.
Freeze immediately (no cover).

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add chopped chilies, soups and sauce. Mix well.
Place tortillas on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with a layer of meat sauce.
Alternate layers.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: chicken casserole(in honor of gladys grattan)
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into a casserole dish. Bake 1 hour more or less at 350°.

title: leslie's crab dip
directions: Cream cheese should be at room temperature.
Clean crab meat of cartilage.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Add crab meat and mix together.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute sliced onions in butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix egg, cottage cheese, flour in mixing bowl.
Combine onions and cheese mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven or until browned on top.

title: adam's grilled cheese
directions: Put oven on broil.
Place slices of bread on cookie sheet. Place in oven about 8-inches from broiler.
Toast one side of bread and remove from oven.
Turn bread over and put 1 slice of cheese on each piece of bread.
Return to broiler until cheese melts and bubbles.

title: senator russell's sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer.
Pour into oblong baking dish that has been buttered.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in small bowl; stir until well blended. Chill.
Refrigerate in tightly covered container.
Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: one cup salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter balls no. 1
directions: Blend peanut
butter and honey.
Stir in dry milk.
Add raisins.
Roll
in small balls.
Roll balls in granola crumbs. Chill well.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Chop green onions very fine.
Soften cream cheese and mix with sour cream and onions.
Spoon about 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons on a tortilla shell and roll.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in about 1 to 2-inch pieces.
Makes 2 dozen.
Serve with salsa.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and 1/2 cup butter.
Set aside to cool.
Cream sugar, remaining butter and eggs.
Add flour, baking soda, buttermilk and candy mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool, then frost.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Beat eggs, add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: confetti lima beans
directions: Cook beans; drain.
Melt butter in a large skillet. Add onions and saute until transparent. Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes. Add pimento and flour.
Stir until flour is smooth. Add sour cream, liquid drained from mushrooms, salt and cooked lima beans. Heat gently.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown sausage, ground beef and oregano.
Drain and add cheese.
Melt with beef and sausage.
Spoon onto bread and place on cookie sheet to freeze.	When ready to serve, place in a 350° oven until mixture is warm or cheese mixture has melted.

title: peanut candy
directions: Blend your butter, milk and sugar and let it come to a complete boil.
Stir until it gets thick and pour over your peanuts on the cookie sheet.

title: meal in a casserole
directions: Mix meat, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Press into a deep baking dish.
Place potatoes on top of meat, then the onion and bell pepper.
Mix soup with can of water and pour over the top. Cover with green beans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: down south pecan pie
directions: Start heating oven to 350°.
Cream butter well in medium mixing bowl.
Add sugar slowly to butter, creaming until light. Slowly stir in syrup, honey, eggs, vanilla and 1 cup nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with rest of nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool.
Good served with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Heat oven
Combine cheese, Bisquick, salt and other seasonings.
Add
oil
and	eggs.
Put
zucchini
in
a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour Bisquick mixture on top.
Bake 25 minutes. Cut in 1 1/2-inch squares.	Serve warm or cool.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, crab, lemon juice and hot sauce. Spread on plate. Top with cocktail sauce. Serve cold.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, lemonade and condensed milk in bowl.
Fill each graham cracker crust with filling.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Mix together well and chill.
Serve with cookies or plain lemon cookies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together (last 6 ingredients).
Peel squash and grate.
Beat well with oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Mix in dry ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in greased loaf pan.
(I use smaller pan and bake less time.)

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Heat soup, milk and Cheez Whiz in saucepan.
Add onion, broccoli and rice.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Wash and trim broccoli.
Separate stalks and cut into bite-size pieces.
In a large saucepan or soup pot over medium heat, saute onion and garlic in butter or oil until the onion is soft but not brown.
Add broccoli (save a few small flowerets for water and garnish), potato, chicken broth, pepper and herbs.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Add bananas, oil, pineapple and juice and nuts.
Stir only to blend (do not beat).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Bake in tube pan or Bundt cake pan.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Saute garlic in oil; add vegetables and cook to desired tenderness, adding bouillon.
Take out vegetables; add cooked chicken.
Mix together and serve.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour and soda; add remaining ingredients.
Stir real good.
Pour into oiled cake pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: leanne's favorite pecan pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cranberry-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda onto waxed paper. Grate orange rind.
Measure and reserve 1 tablespoon. Squeeze juice into 2-cup measure and add boiling water to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Stir in reserved orange rind and shortening until shortening is melted.
Beat eggs in a large bowl until foamy. Gradually beat in sugar and continue to beat until mixture is thick and light.
Stir dry ingredients into egg mixture alternately with orange mixture, blending well.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Turn out from pan and cool completely.

title: sherried cream of portabello mushroom soup
directions: Quarter and thinly slice mushrooms and chop onion.
In a heavy saucepan, cook mushrooms and onion in butter over moderate heat.
Stirring occasionally, until softened and any liquid mushrooms give off is evaporated.
Add water and cream and simmer 15 minutes.
In a blende, puree half of the mixture (using caution when blending hot liquids) and stir puree, sherry, salt and pepper into the mixture remaining in the pan.
Heat soup until hot and stir in chives.
Serves 2 as first course.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Mix soup, water, milk and onion together.
Pour over raw rice.
Put broccoli on top.
Melt cheese with oleo.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with 8 ounces Cheddar and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Use oblong glass baking dish.

title: brandy cream sauce
directions: Combine sugar, water and salt in a medium size saucepan and bring to a slow simmer.
Hold there for about 10 minutes; set aside.
Combine egg mixture, cream, brandy and orange rind. Gradually add the sugar syrups to the egg and cream mixture, stirring constantly until it is cooled and thickened.
Serve over sponge or pound cake.
Makes 2 cups sauce.

title: campfire chicken
directions: Salt and pepper the chicken to taste. Wrap all ingredients in foil. Cook at 400° for 1 hour. Prepare 1 wrapped package per person.

title: melt away
directions: Cut English muffins into
8 pieces, each muffin.
Mix 1 stick butter or margarine,
Old
English	sharp cheese, mayonnaise, seasoned salt,
garlic
salt and shrimp or crab.
Blend all together and
spread
on
muffins
pieces.	Freeze for 1/2 hour. Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 15 minutes.	May refrigerate or freeze.

title: stuffed noodle shells
directions: Boil noodles in salted water until done.
Drain on paper towel, then stuff with salad and serve with crackers or melba toast.

title: microwave stuffed mushrooms
directions: For each of the following stuffings, use 12 large fresh mushrooms (2-inches in diameter).
Wash mushrooms well; remove stems and reserve them; dry.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, place chopped stems and onion; cover.
Microwave at High 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.
To hot mixture, add cream cheese, mashing and mixing well.
Stir in ham and bacon.
On a microwave-safe plate, arrange caps in a circle; microwave at High 3 to 4 minutes, rotating plate 1/2 turn after 2 minutes.
Divide stuffing evenly among caps and mound slightly.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add well beaten eggs, add flour and cinnamon. Stir in apples, raisins and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crusty brie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With serrated knife, carefully cut off top of bread and save.
Cut down through bread, but leave shell intact (about 1/2-inch thick on sides and bottom crust).
Be careful not to cut through the bottom crust.
Pick out chunks of bread inside of
loaf and tear top into chunks also.
They should be thick.
Around rim of shell, with knife, make cuts 1 1/2-inches deep and 1 1/2 inches apart.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix peach juice with pudding until well blended.
Set aside. Add all other ingredients with pudding mixture.
Stir well. Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Mix thoroughly together.
Separate into 2 or 3 balls.
Roll in paprika or crushed walnuts.

title: party punch
directions: Precool ingredients.
Mix in punch bowl.
Add champagne last. Add ice.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water.
Add 2 cups flour and salt.
Mix well. Add slightly beaten eggs, honey and melted oleo.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour, mixing well.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Slice chicken into cublets if they're thick.
Beat egg with water.
Dip chicken into egg batter, then into bread crumbs. Saute in hot oil in frying pan until golden brown.
Mix sauce and drained mushrooms.
Pour a layer of sauce into a greased casserole dish; add chicken and remaining sauce.
Can be covered and refrigerated at this point, if desired.

title: chicken and green noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken; cut in bite size pieces.
Save chicken stock. Saute onion, celery and pepper in oil.
Blend in cheese and soup. Add mushrooms and olives.
Boil noodles in chicken stock and let them soak up the stock.
Blend all ingredients and heat to serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Pour all the ingredients over the squash.
Place herb seasoning stuffing on top; also pour the butter on top of the stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: angel icing
directions: Beat egg white in small mixer bowl at high speed until stiff. Mix vinegar, sugar, Karo and water in a pot.
Bring to a boil. Add food coloring, if desired. While beating egg whites, pour boiling syrup over egg whites very slowly. Add vanilla.

title: hot spinach salad
directions: Cut bacon in 1 inch pieces; brown.
Remove from pan and drain. Hard boil 1 egg; shell and grate.
To bacon fat, add vinegar, water and sugar.
Heat to boiling.
Beat 1 egg in bowl and stir slowly into hot mixture.
Pour hot dressing over fresh spinach.
Sprinkle with bacon, grated egg and croutons.
Serve at once.

title: today's poke salad
directions: Wash greens. Pat dry. Combine greens, onions and turkey bacon in salad bowl. Toss well. Serve with nonfat Italian dressing. Makes 8 servings.

title: banana cake
directions: Use standard method of mixing.
Bake in layers or I use one 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Good plain, iced or with whipped cream.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Mix all together.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Bake pie shell for 5 minutes on preheated cookie sheet. Combine sugar, eggs and butter.
Beat well.
Add flour, buttermilk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet (to prevent "soggy" crust) at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and bring to boil.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Pack in clean, hot jars and seal.

title: phyllis' french coconut pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients and cook, uncovered, on low heat for 15 minutes.
Cool, then chill.
Spoon into dishes and serve with light cream, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Put dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add sugar.
Pour oil into center of dry ingredients.
Break eggs into mixture.
Add vanilla and chocolate.
Mix well.
Add nuts and chips.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake dark fudge cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Poke holes in cake and pour 1 cup strong coffee over cake (1 cup Kahlua may be used instead of coffee).

title: lenten orange cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon twice.
In bowl, combine oil, sugar, orange juice and grated rind of orange. Slowly add flour mixture.
Then add raisins and nuts.
Place in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Watch carefully after 30 minutes.
When cool, sift top of cake with powdered sugar and cinnamon.

title: chrystal's easy bread
directions: Add and mix with electric mixer.
For flour, I use white, whole wheat, oat or a combination.
Add a cup of flour and mix with mixer.
Continue adding flour until dough is elastic.

title: lemon cake for lazy ladies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
(I add 1 tablespoon each of lemon flavoring and lemon juice because I like a really lemony flavor.) Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool completely.
Slice across cake into 3 sections.
Divide a can of pie filling into 3 parts.
Cover tops of each sliced of cake with filling.
Frost sides and hole with Cool Whip and refrigerate.
May be garnished as you wish, either lemon zest or almonds.
I have used both.
Hope you enjoy!

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Set aside. Cook broccoli according to directions on box.
Drain.
Saute the celery and onions in 1/2 stick margarine.
Add Cheez Whiz, soup, water and broccoli.
Add rice.
Put in oven and bake, covered, for 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add dates, sugar and eggs.
Cook, stirring constantly, until dates are melted.
Add pecans and Rice Krispies.
Cool.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cook eggs.
Cool under cold running water.
Peel shells from eggs.
Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Mash yolks with remaining ingredients except paprika until mixture is smooth.
Fill whites with this mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 6.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Crumble ground beef in large glass bowl.
Cook on High 2 to 3 minutes, or until beef is browned; stir once.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.
Cook at High 4 to 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Meanwhile, combine Ricotta, egg, salt and pepper.
Spoon 1/2 cup sauce in 12 x 8-inch dish.
Alternately layer noodles, egg mixture, Mozzarella and sauce, forming 3 layers.
Cook, covered with plastic wrap on High 8 minutes and on Medium-low 35 to 38 minutes, or until noodles are tender.
If necessary, shield ends of dish with foil during last 10 minutes of cooking time.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; let stand, covered, 15 minutes before serving.

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Cut steak into pieces.
Roll in flour.
Put in bottom of crock-pot.
Stir soya sauce and molasses together and spoon over meat.
Cover with layers of onion rings, sliced mushrooms and green peppers.
Add tomatoes over everything.
Cook on low setting for eight hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add all of the milk and vanilla.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick, over low flame or over boiling water in double boiler.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made with whites from eggs and 2 tablespoons sugar per egg.
Brown in a 400° oven.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream
cheese
with
sugar
and egg yolks.
Whip cream; add vanilla
and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff, fold into cream. Add to cheese mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: chicken baked in rice
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Combine rice, soup mix and water in a baking dish.
Arrange chicken over rice; dot with margarine.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: raspberries mint punch
directions: Combine all together in punch bowl.
Serve very cold.
Serves 14 or 15 people.

title: pineapple slaw
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine pineapple and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add dressing quickly after cutting apple so the apple will not darken.
Combine reserved juice and mayonnaise; add to cabbage mixture, tossing gently.
Cover and chill.

title: salmon confetti
directions: Prepare dinner according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Place in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Fry sausage first and pour off grease.
Melt margarine, saute celery, onions and parsley.
Add sausage, stock and eggs.
Mix together.
Stuff bird or bake in covered casserole dish.
Bake at 350°.

title: western-style asparagus
directions: Prepare asparagus by cutting or breaking off the hard part. Cut in 1 or 2-inch pieces.
Steam until tender (about 10 minutes). While asparagus is cooking, cube bread slices and saute in a large frying pan with butter.
Brown bread cubes, then add asparagus and mix evenly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9x13 inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together except marshmallow cream and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes or until done.
While cake is hot, pour marshmallow cream over top.
Let cake cool and then frost.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix and roll into pieces about 1-inch in diameter.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cut in slices about 1/4-inch thick.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate covered pretzels
directions: Combine chocolate chips and shortening in a mixing bowl. Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until melted; stir until smooth.
Carefully remove chocolate from microwave.
Dip pretzels into the melted chocolate and place on waxed paper.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts (optional).

title: orange-cheese congealed salad
directions: Mix jello in boiling water.
Add grated cheese and stir well; set aside.
Mix milk, pineapple and mayonnaise.
Stir well to get mayonnaise lumps out.
Add this to jello-cheese mixture, mixing well.
Pour into bowl or mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix the Cool Whip, milk and lemonade together.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
This is a cool, refreshing dessert for summer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: famous banana punch(serves 50)
directions: Combine water (8 cups) and sugar. Boil 15 minutes and let cool.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice, 6 cans of water, lemon juice and bananas. Freeze mixture.
Add ginger ale at serving time. (Remove from freezer at least 2 hours ahead of serving time. Sometimes thawing takes longer depending on container size.)

title: nut salad and dressing
directions: Add sugar, flour and chili powder; mix together.
Beat in egg, butter and salt to taste.
Add water and vinegar; cook until thick. Shred cabbage, apple and nuts.
Add salt; mix, then add to mix.

title: aunt julia's squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Crumble crackers.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian noodle bake
directions: Prepare egg noodles according to package.
In a large skillet, combine sausage, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until sausage is no longer pink.
Drain and stir in rest of ingredients, except cheese.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients together and blend thoroughly.
Pour into 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add all dry ingredients.
Then add carrots, pineapple and rest of ingredients.
Pour into 3 cake pans (or make 2 loaves).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for loaves or for 45 minutes for pans.
Check for doneness.

title: impossible french apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Mix apples and spices; turn into pie plate.
Beat rest of ingredients, except streusel, until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Sprinkle with streusel.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and cream cheese. Add crushed pineapple. Stir well. Fold in whipped topping; stir. In large Pyrex long dish, add the graham cracker mix. Pat to all sides of dish. Add the pineapple mixture. Refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours before eating. You can sprinkle ground graham crackers on top.

title: golden chicken with noodles
directions: Mix soup, water, lemon juice, mustard, garlic and carrots in slow cooker.
Add chicken and turn to coat.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 8 hours or until done.
Serve over noodles.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Whip egg whites.
Slowly add sugar.
Stir in chips and pecans. Preheat oven to 400°.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Turn oven off; place cookies in oven and leave in overnight.

title: molasses butterball cookies
directions: In mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine on medium speed of electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Add molasses and beat until fluffy.
Add flour to butter mixture; beat at low speed until well blended.
Stir in nuts.

title: pepper steak
directions: In wok or electric skillet, melt butter; add beef and garlic. Saute until browned. Remove meat. Saute onions and peppers, then stir in meat, tomatoes and bouillon cube.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. In a bowl, blend water, cornstarch, soy sauce, salt and sugar. Add to meat mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Serve over rice.

title: frothy orange drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender. Cover and process until drink is thick and slushy. Yield: 4 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Remove chicken and skin from bones; cut into pieces.
Mix stuffing with melted margarine.
Grease flat casserole dish. Layer stuffing, then chicken and mushroom soup, diluted with 1 cup of broth.
Repeat layers using cream of chicken soup and 1 cup of broth.
Top with some reserved stuffing mix.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix the first five ingredients in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Do not grease pan.
Stir with spoon.
Make 3 holes, 1 hole larger than the other 2.
Add melted Crisco in large hole, vinegar in one hole and vanilla in other hole.
Pour cold water over all and stir well.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes (in pan which it was mixed).
Ice with desired icing.

title: easy chicken cordon bleu
directions: Tenderize to flatten each chicken breast.
Lightly season with salt and pepper.
Use 1/4 teaspoon sage on each chicken breast. Layer one piece of ham and cheese on each breast.
Fold and roll up.
Beat eggs and milk together, carefully roll each chicken breast through egg/milk mixture.
Then place each side in bread crumbs.
Once all chicken breasts have been coated, place in skillet with 4 tablespoons canola oil.
Cook on medium heat until golden brown.
Remove from skillet; place rolls into oblong baking dish.
Prepare Hollandaise sauce per package instructions.
Pour over rolls in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Beat together the eggs and cream cheese until creamy. Stir in cottage cheese.
In a rectangular cake pan, take approximately 4 noodles and lay in bottom of pan.
Evenly spread half of the cream cheese mixture over the noodles.
Next sprinkle half of the Mozzarella
cheese and finally half of the sauce and the remaining ingredients. Repeat the steps with a second layer. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: candle salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce.
Strain and set berries aside. Dissolve gelatin in hot juice and water.
Add salt and lemon juice.
Chill until it begins to gel.
Beat mayonnaise into gelatin with rotary beater until light and fluffy.	Fold in cranberries, apple and nuts.
Divide mixture evenly into 10 empty 6-ounce juice cans.
Fill each can 3/4 full.
Chill and unmold. Garnish with mayonnaise.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: speedy goulash
directions: Brown beef, pour in all ingredients, except macaroni.
Bring to a boil.
Pour in macaroni and simmer 15 minutes or until noodles are soft.

title: apple oat krunch
directions: Stir together 1 cup flour, sugar, yeast, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add the water and butter and beat at medium speed about 2 minutes.
Add eggs and another cup of flour.
Beat for 2 minutes. Stir in remaining flour and oats.
Spoon batter into two well-greased 9-inch cake pans.
Cover; let rise until double in size.
Arrange apple slices on top of batter.
Sprinkle with streusel.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: strawberry salad mold
directions: Add boiling water to jello to dissolve.
Stir in frozen strawberries until they separate.
Add undrained pineapple.
Stir in sliced bananas.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture in a 8- inch or 9-inch square pan.
Chill until thickened.
Leave remaining 1/2 jello mixture at room temperature.
When chilled mixture is thickened, remove from refrigerator and spread with sour cream. Pour remaining jello mixture over this.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill to set.
Delicious and pretty, too.

title: light cheese cake
directions: Mix the jello with the boiling water. Add the lemon juice. Cool.
Chill the Milnot.
Whip until
stiff. Add jello and sugar. In a separate bowl, whip the cream cheese.
Add 1/4 cup Milnot mixture to cream cheese.
Transfer cream cheese mixture to total Milnot. Whip until smooth.
Prepare a graham cracker crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour whipped mixture over crust and refrigerate overnight. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.

title: autumn turkey pie
directions: Saute desired amount of onion in margarine. Sprinkle in flour. Cook and stir for a few minutes. Gradually add broth. Add thyme and Tabasco. Cook, stirring constantly, until it boils and begins to thicken. Place pastry in pie plate. Pour sauce, meat and vegetable mixture in pie plate. Top with crust. Crimp edges and slash top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. This can be made with one pie crust and baked in a 9 x 12 baking dish, placing the pie crust on top.

title: give-away cookie mix
directions: This recipe is a dry cookie mix that you can give away as a gift.
Mix all of the above dry ingredients and divide into small plastic bags, about 2 cups of mix to a bag (Ziploc bags work best). Write the following instructions to go with each bag of dry mix:

title: "ting-a-ling's"
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Pour chocolate on noodles; mix gently until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Chill to harden.

title: strawberry cheesecake dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl of electric mixer.
Beat until smooth. Great dip for fruit or pound cake pieces.

title: pineapple upside-down carrot cake
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar.
Put pineapple over sugar.
Prepare cake mix as on box.
Pour over sugar-pineapple mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in oven at 350°. Let cool 10 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix well. Flour and grease loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sandra's junk cake
directions: Punch cake full of holes with wooden handle of spoon.
Mix jello with 1/2 cup hot water until dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour over cake.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Pour it over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over entire cake.
Then put cherry pie filling over the cake.
You may put walnuts or pecans on top if desired.
Chill, cut and enjoy.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; hard boil the eggs and then cut all into potato salad size pieces. Add about 1/2 cup of the dressing and 1/2 cup of the sandwich spread and mix well. If too dry, add equal parts of dressing and spread. Cover and let chill overnight for best results.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice according to instructions.
Saut onions and peppers in olive oil.
Remove.
Cook hamburger until done.
Cook chorizo. (Might need more olive oil.)
Combine all ingredients, except grated cheese.
Put into baking dish and put cheese over top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: sunday chicken and rice bake
directions: In a bowl, stir together soup, milk and onion soup mix. Reserve 1 cup of soup mix for later. Stir in uncooked rice and vegetables. Turn rice mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange chicken on top.
Pour reserved soup and onion soup mix over chicken and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil and bake at 355° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours until rice is tender.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese, 1/2 cup grated Mozzarella cheese, grated Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and egg together.
Cook stuffing shells according to directions; drain well.

title: pork chops and scalloped potatoes
directions: I'm going to plant a spring garden this year.
Here is the recipe:

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Take out 1/3 cup flour.
Mix in cup with the 1/4 cup water to form a paste.
Add Crisco to remaining flour.
Cut Criso and flour until it almost forms a ball.
Add the paste mixture to flour and Crisco.
Mix well until dough forms a ball.
Roll out between floured towel.
Cook at 400° until lightly browned.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat with onion, garlic powder, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add tomato sauce and chili powder.
Let simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Coat meat with flour.
Heat oil in 3-quart saucepan.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in salt, pepper, soup, milk and water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add frozen vegetables; return to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: apple cups with sweet potatoes
directions: Pare top and core large apples.
Boil water and sugar in saucepan.
When sugar is dissolved, add apples and cook gently until tender.
Don't overcook.
When the apples are cool enough to handle, hollow out and reserve the removed pulp.
Cook sweet potatoes, peel and mash with butter, salt and little milk if necessary.
Add this mixture to the mashed apple pulp and fill the apples.
Place the apples in a baking dish with a little apple syrup.
Heat in 375° oven for 10 minutes.
If prepared ahead of time, cover with wax paper and chill in refrigerator.
This is a delicious dish to serve at a holiday meal, especially with turkey.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Put hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch pan; add onions and margarine.
Combine sour cream, Cheez Whiz and cream of chicken soup.
Spread over top of potatoes.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve warm.

title: wreck on the mountain
directions: Put oil in large skillet. Finely chop all ingredients. Fry until done (making sure potatoes are done). Serve with any meat or by itself with ketchup or beans and cornbread.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease tube pan. Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat 2 minutes.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt and add to egg mixture alternately with sour cream.
Spread 1/3 of batter in tube pan. Sprinkle with 1/3 of the filling and repeat two more times. Bake 60 minutes.

title: mud cookies
directions: Combine in saucepan sugar, milk, butter, salt and cocoa. Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Pour mix over oats and mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper and cool.

title: apple pineapple scallop
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve 3/4 cup juice.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and reserved pineapple juice in heavy saucepan.
Cook stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat, stir in lemon juice and set aside.
Layer fruit, crumbs and cheese in buttered 2 quart casserole.
Pour on liquid before adding last layer of crumbs and cheese.
Cover and bake at 350°
for about 1 hour or until apple slices are tender.
Serve hot with pork or any meat or warm as a dessert.

title: farmers salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese, eggs, tomatoes, cucumber, onion, green pepper, and ranch dressing.
Gently fold together.
Serve over lettuce with crackers.

title: walnut glory cake
directions: Sift flour with cinnamon and salt; beat egg whites (1 1/4 cups) in large mixing bowl until soft mounds form.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar.
Continue beating until very stiff, straight peaks form.
Do not underbeat.
Combine egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla in small bowl.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Fold batter gently but thoroughly into egg whites using a wire whip or spatula.
Fold in walnuts.
Turn into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes. Invert immediately.
Cool completely before removing from pan. Frost with a vanilla glaze; sprinkle with 4x sugar or serve with whipped cream.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine the
zucchini, onions and salt; let stand for 6 hours. Drain and rinse.
Grind the green and red peppers; add to the zucchini mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes, stirring well.
Pack in canning jars.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes; cut into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Moisten potatoes with water; shake a few at a time in the bag, coating the potatoes with the cheese mixture.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place potatoes in one layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn once during baking.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Melt margarine.
Mix all other ingredients.
Bake in deep casserole dish at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: skroodles
directions: *No other brands will taste as good!

title: special k candy
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and butter together; bring to boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Pour over Special K cereal.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoons onto wax paper.

title: coffee can pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix all liquids.
Stir until smooth. Grease and flour four 1-pound coffee cans.
Fill half full; bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: imitation colonel sanders' chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a paper sack.
Dip chicken in milk, then into sack.
Shake sack to evenly coat chicken.
Fry in skillet with a lot of grease.
Leave the lid partially open.

title: easy pecan coffee cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of pecans in bottom of pan.
In small saucepan, bring margarine, brown sugar and remaining nuts to a boil.
Set aside. Use one 10 ounce package of biscuits and one half of 5 ounce package.
Cut biscuits in half; roll into balls and arrange in Bundt pan.
Pour half of the brown sugar syrup over the balls. Repeat with the remaining biscuits.
Pour the remaining syrup over the balls of dough.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly brown.
Invert on waxed paper immediately.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and peel if skin is thick or tough.
Put potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Put potatoes into a baking dish.
Fan them slightly.
Drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Serves 4.

title: tempura(servings:  4)
directions: Remove head and shell of shrimp.
Slice vegetables.
Place in water for 1/2 hour.
Make batter just before cooking.
Beat egg; add ice water and flour.
Mix with chopsticks.
Do not overmix. Heat oil in a deep pan to about 370°.
Coat materials in batter. Start with shrimp and then vegetables.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Add sugar and butter and cook until tender.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in large casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: southern pancake special
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, milk, eggs and nutmeg in a bowl.
Beat together leaving batter a bit lumpy.
Melt butter in a 9-inch ovenproof skillet.
Saute apples in butter then pour in water.
Place skillet in oven and bake 15 minutes until pancake is golden and puffed.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with sugar. Return to oven for 2 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Serve with jelly or jam if desired.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: grape broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Layer as follows:
lasagna noodles, ground chuck, 1/2 large sauce, layer noodles, all of cottage cheese mixture, layer of noodles, remaining 1/2 of sauce, Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Chill evaporated milk overnight in refrigerator. Crush vanilla wafers until fine. Dissolve jello, hot water, sugar, juice from lemon and lemon rind and refrigerate until almost set. Whip evaporated milk until stiff. When jello mixture is slightly congealed, add whipped evaporated milk and mix. Put half crushed vanilla wafers into pan (9 x 13). Add jello mixture and spread remaining crushed wafers on top. Chill 3 hours or overnight.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Use the almonds and bread crumbs as topping.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Add vegetables; boil an additional 10 minutes.
Add soup and cheese; heat until cheese is melted.

title: settler's beans
directions: Brown the hamburg, onion and bacon lightly in pan.
Combine the meat mixture in a large dish or pan with the beans.
Add the remaining ingredients to the mixture.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or cook slowly on top of stove for 1 hour.

title: diabetic sugarless cookies
directions: Boil raisins, dates and apples in one scant cup of water for three minutes.
Add shortening.
Cool.
Add beaten eggs, sweetener, vanilla and soda.
Add flour and nuts last.
Mix well.
Chill dough overnight in refrigerator in covered pan.
Drop by teaspoon on well-greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Store in refrigerator in tightly covered container.

title: mom's special ranger cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugars.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix well.
Then add oatmeal, coconut, rice crispies and chocolate chips.
Mix carefully.
Drop by teaspoons onto baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° until light brown around edges, 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookies should be soft and chewy.

title: company crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Pour milk over bread crumbs to soften; add remaining ingredients except eggs. Stir in eggs. Pour mixture into a well-greased loaf pan or a 6 x 8-inch casserole. Set the dish in a container of hot water and bake for about 45 minutes or until an inserted knife comes out clean. Serves 6.

title: great guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender until smooth.
(Reserve 1 or 2 seeds from avocados to place in the dip to prevent darkening.)
Don't forget to remove before serving.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in hot water.
Add Jell-O and applesauce. Let set.

title: nutmeg cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients, add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour, beating well after each addition. Stir in vanilla extract.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add milk and soda (dissolved in small amount of water).
Add bananas, flour and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: christmas pot pourri
directions: Cook on stove at simmer, makes your house smell great.
May be kept in refrigerator in closed jar.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Drain the fruit and mix the ingredients.
Serve chilled.

title: reindeer droppings
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Make into balls.
Dip into the following that has been melted together in a double boiler:
1 cup semi-sweet morsels and 1/2 stick paraffin.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: savory shrimp salad
directions: Gently mix all ingredients.
Use just enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Serve on bed of lettuce.
Garnish with olives.

title: banana bread
directions: In a bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and soda, and set aside.
In another bowl, cream together the sugar and the margarine or butter.
Add the eggs and beat well.
Stir in the mashed bananas.
Add the dry ingredients and the nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, then reduce the heat to 325° and bake another 35 minutes.
Let set 20 minutes before inverting onto a rack to cool.

title: jackie zehender's chocolate delight
directions: Melt Hershey's chocolate with margarine, then cool.
Add 4 cups sifted powdered sugar, egg yolks and nuts.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites and fold into chocolate mixture; mix.
Lay vanilla wafers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour chocolate mixture over wafers. Slice ice cream brick into 1/2-inch slabs and lay over mixture. Top with crushed vanilla wafers.
Freeze.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Mix broth, water, green onions and soy sauce in 1 1/2-quart pot.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Pour eggs into mixture. Stir gently until eggs form strings. Serve with fried noodles.

title: daddy's deer roast
directions: Place roast in baking bag.
Slice apples and onions and place on roast.
Add all other ingredients in bag.
Seal bag and punch a few holes in it.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350° until tender.

title: dutch potato soup
directions: Saute onion in oil in soup kettle.
Add potatoes and enough water to cover; simmer until tender.
Add evaporated milk, bring just to a boil and gently stir in cottage cheese.
Top with chopped parsley to serve.

title: mary's strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and
cornstarch until clear.
Add dry Jell-O and food coloring, after
taking
off heat.
Cool.
Put strawberries in baked pie shell; pour mixture over.
Let stand 5 1/2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: happy trail dog biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Place oven rack in upper third of oven. Line a cookie sheet with foil.
In a large bowl, mix flours, oats, corn meal, liver powder, salt and garlic powder.
Add egg, oil and broth.
Mix with a wooden spoon to make a soft dough.
Dough should be soft but firm enough to roll out.
If too moist, add some flour; if too dry, add water.
On floured surface, roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness and cut in 3 1/2-inch long dog bone biscuit shapes with floured cutter.
Place 1-inch apart on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 2 hours.
Turn off oven and let biscuits stand in oven overnight to dry out and harden.
Can be stored in plastic bags at room temperature up to 3 months.
Makes about 24.
Per biscuit:
31 calories, 6 grams protein, 23 grams carbohydrates, 5 grams fat, 12 mg. cholesterol and 142 mg. sodium.

title: butter balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls (walnut sized).
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool for 5 minutes.
Roll into confectioners sugar.

title: cashaw
directions: Peel cashaw and cut up in cube size pieces.
Place in Corning Ware baking dish.
Add sugar, water and oleo; sprinkle good with nutmeg.
Cover and cook slowly until slightly tender.
Test with fork.
Remove lid; raise fire and cook until done and juice has thickened.
May also be cooked in oven.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together well and chill.
You may want to add some pineapple juice.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in a 12-inch tube pan.

title: onion soup
directions: Melt butter in a large pot, add onions and cook very slowly, about 45 minutes, over low heat, stirring often.
Stir in sugar, flour and cook for 3 minutes.
Add water and simmer partially covered for 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Boil dates, prunes and raisins in 1 cup water for 3 minutes. Add margarine and let cool.
Mix flour, soda, salt and spices, sifting together.
Mix with fruit mixture.
Add eggs, nuts and vanilla.
Stir with spoon (do not use mixer) to blend.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a 10-inch skillet at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: easy apple pie dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread pie filling evenly.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over all of this. Melt butter/margarine and drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned on top.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain and add seasoning.
Add all the cans (undrained).
Heat and garnish with sour cream, shredded cheese and taco chips as desired.

title: seafood stew
directions: Scald hake in boiling water and place in bottom of earthenware (or any other) pot.
Saute onion and tomatoes in olive oil seasoned with salt.
Cover hake with this mixture.
Simmer over low heat until hake is cooked.
Cut lobster in slices and add.
Add langostinos, prawns, clams, peas and red pepper flakes.
Cover pot and cook until clam shells open.
Serves 4.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, water, yeast, salt and well beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup flour at a time, beating after each cup.
Let rise and make into rolls and let rise again.
Bake in 420° oven until brown.

title: chinese barbecue spareribs
directions: Arrange ribs in large roasting pan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over ribs.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, turning ribs once or twice.
Transfer ribs to grill.
Reserve sauce.
Set grill as high above gray coals as possible.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes or until meat is browned and tender, turning and basting frequently with sauce.

title: ice cream jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water in spoonfuls.
Stir in ice cream until completely melted.
Drain oranges.
Add to top of Jell-O.
Refrigerate.

title: beet nut salad
directions: Drain liquid from beets and pineapple, heat and dissolve the sugar and fruit flavored gelatin in heated liquid.
Mix well.
Add remaining liquids.
Chill until syrupy.
Stir in beets, pineapple and nuts.
Finish chilling.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; roll into small balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Press 1 Hershey's Kiss in the center of each ball.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool on sheet before removing.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in milk, then roll dough jelly roll fashion with sausage layer in the middle. Cut in 1/2-inch slices and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheesy mexican chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13 pan. Mix soup, 1 1/2 cups cheese, milk and seasoning mix. Spoon over chicken. Top with chips. Cover. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Remove cover. Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Melt oleo; add onion and chives; saute.
Add sour cream and cheese; stir and mix.
Add potatoes.

title: one bowl cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in vanilla and 2/3 cup milk.
Beat in shortening until all ingredients are smooth and well blended.
Beat in 1/3 cup milk and eggs.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mini-meat loaves
directions: Combine all ingredients except ketchup in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Place about 1/3 c. of meat mixture in each muffin cup to make 12 miniature meat loaves.
Top each with ketchup. Bake at 350 for 35 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, butter, milk and vanilla until it comes to full rolling boil for 5 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients with liquid mixture and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper and let set until cooled.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch or larger pan.
Chill. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Dip into melted chocolate and cool on wax paper.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and salt.
Cut the stick of butter and the cheese loaf into small chunks.
Stir these into the soup mixture.
In a large bowl, mix in the onion and thawed hash browns.
Bake in a large baking pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice.
Saute onion in butter.
Cook broccoli as on back of box.
After onion is sauteed, add soup and a can of water.
When soup is smooth, add cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Butter a casserole dish.
Combine all ingredients in dish.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling into 8 x 13-inch pan.
Next, distribute pineapple over filling (juice and all).
Sprinkle dry cake mix over all, creating next layer. Cut butter into patties and lay on top.
Sprinkle with coconut and/or nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barazit (flat sesame seed cookie)
directions: Brown sesame seed under broiler until golden.
Cool and set aside.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix ingredients as for fruit cake.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Test for doneness.
Turn out on rack when cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir in 2 cups of rhubarb, cut in small pieces.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit medley
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl; refrigerate until serving. Top with nuts. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: honey dijon ham
directions: Heat oven to 325 degrees.
Place ham in large shallow roasting pan.
Bake until meat thermometer inserted in thickest part registers 125 degrees, about 1 1/4 hours.
Remove from oven, trim off rind, leaving very thin layer all around.
Score ham by cutting diamond shapes 1/4-inch deep into ham.
Combine honey, mustard and cloves in a small bowl.
Spoon honey mixture over ham, and into diamond cuts.
Continue baking about 30 minutes, or until meat thermometer registers 140 degrees.
Serve with additional warm glaze, if desired.
Serves 12.

title: dan's cream chicken
directions: Mix milk and soup in hot pan.
Sprinkle pepper and salt in and stir.
Put chicken in soup until done.
Serve.

title: mom's heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat
juice from pears.
In blender, put Jell-O, juice, pears, cream
cheese and nuts.
Blend until pears are pulverized.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Put in shallow pan that has been sprayed with Pam for easy removal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first seven ingredients in bowl.
Crunch up chips and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over chips.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 300° until done.
Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk until stiff; add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dudley's carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: cooked chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan. Bring to rolling boil, stirring often, and boil approximately 2 minutes (firm-ball stage). Be sure your cake is completely cooled before icing it.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix everything together real good and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cover dish with foil. Uncover to brown.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions and drain.
Combine with tomato sauce, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Place in casserole dish and put sliced cheese on the meat; top with biscuits.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: chili-fried corn
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook, stirring frequently, until onions start to brown, about 3 minutes.
Add corn and chilies.
Cook, stirring frequently, 5 minutes.
Remove skillet from heat and sprinkle cheese evenly over corn.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes to melt cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry cheese cake pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Chill.
Add almond flavor to pie filling and carefully spoon over cheese layer.
Chill until set.

title: scalloped crab
directions: In one bowl, mix white sauce, catsup, Worcestershire, salt and pepper. In 2nd bowl, crab, mushrooms, peppers, cheese and crackers. Combine both bowls and pour in casserole dish. Sprinkle paprika and cut pieces of margarine across top of casserole. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: grandma d.'s cheese ball
directions: Set cream cheese and Cheddar cheese out so they're at room temperature and softened.
Combine all ingredients well, using a mixer.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Shape into 2 balls.
Chop 1/2 cup nuts and roll the cheese balls in them.

title: fruity french toast fritters
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg until foamy. Add milk and beat well. In a micro-safe bowl, place apple juice, cinnamon and raisins; heat on High for 90 seconds. Allow to cool.

title: zucchini fritters(serves 4)
directions: Using the large holes of a box grater, grate zucchini into a medium bowl. Add salt, lemon zest, chopped parsley, garlic, pepper and eggs. Mix well to combine. Slowly add flour, stirring so no lumps form. Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large saut pan over medium-high heat until oil sizzles when you drop a small amount of zucchini mixture into the pan. Carefully drop about 2 tablespoons zucchini mixture into pan; repeat, spacing fritters a few inches apart.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Leave cream cheese out overnight to soften.
Mix Dream Whip. Add sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Then mix in cream cheese until mixture is smooth.
Layer crust, Dream Whip, cherries, Dream Whip and cherries.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Prepare white sauce by melting 4 ounces butter with 2 tablespoons flour.
Stir in 1 cup milk until thick and bubbly. Add crab meat and stir to blend.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 325° until slightly browned.

title: three steps of heaven
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into pan.
Bake until firm at 350°.
Cream together cheese and sugar until spreadable. Spread cheese on crust.
Mix pudding as on box.
Pour pudding on top of cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: lemon gremolata dressing
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together all ingredients until blended. Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven.
Good eating and they freeze well.

title: jenny's pressure cooked english roast beef
directions: Check your 4-quart pressure cooker for safety.
Heat cooker; add 3 tablespoons cooking oil.
Brown roast on all sides; it may be necessary to cut the roast into 2 pieces.
Once roast is browned, remove from cooker and place the cooking rack into the cooker.
Now place the browned roast back into the cooker.
Season the roast with salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion soup mix. Chop up the medium onion and add at this time.
If you plan on having carrots and potatoes, have them cut (quartered) and place them in the cooker.
Remember not to fill the cooker over 2/3 full at any time.
Add water to put the cooker 2/3 full.
Close cover securely.

title: evelyn's tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Roll and cut into bite sized pieces.
They can be stored in the refrigerator overnight.
Spiral design finger food appetizer.

title: berried delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine.
Press firmly onto bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: lemon herb chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, lemon pepper seasoning and dill weed. Dip chicken breasts in beaten egg and then in seasoned bread crumbs.
Pan-fry in 2 tablespoons oil 15 minutes or until browned.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cupcakes
directions: Into bowl sift together flour, cinnamon, brown sugar, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
In a large bowl with mixer beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until thick and pale.
Stir in zucchini and flour mixture until batter is combined well.
Fold in walnuts and chips.
Spoon into 1/3 cup muffin tins lined with paper baking cups, filling cups 1/2 way. Bake cupcakes in a preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Let cool in tins 5 minutes.
Turn out onto racks and cool completely.

title: nut-cracker sweets
directions: Turn the oven to 350°.
Tear off a 15-inch pieces of foil. Line the baking pan with the foil.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar.
Arrange graham crackers side by side.
Stir the brown sugar mixture.
Spoon the brown sugar mixture over the graham crackers.
Sprinkle the crackers with the nut topping. Bake for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: smooth "n" creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk. Beat one minute. Fold in whipped topping. Makes 4 cups. Store frosted cake in refrigerator.

title: no-cook marshmallow frosting
directions: Beat egg whites and salt with electric beater until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until smooth and glossy.
Continue beating and add Karo syrup a little at a time, until frosting peaks.
Fold in vanilla.
Makes enough frosting for 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: butterscotch chewy cake
directions: Beat eggs with rotary beater in top of double boiler until blended.
Blend in brown sugar and butter.
Place over rapidly boiling water, stirring constantly, just until hot (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add all at once to cooked mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Turn into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) 23 to 30 minutes until it springs back.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar while warm.

title: strawberry spread
directions: Combine strawberries, 1/2 cup water, lemon juice and cinnamon in a small Dutch oven; stirring well, bring to a boil.
Dissolve cornstarch in remaining 1/4 cup water and stir into boiling mixture.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 or 3 minutes or until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in sugar substitute.
Diabetic exchange: free up to 1 tablespoon.

title: date balls
directions: Combine dates, sugar, egg and oleo in boiler; cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies; shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: patricia's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; remove from heat.
Drain and mash.
Mix ingredients together.
Place in a bowl and top with bacon bits.

title: peach pecan pie
directions: Crush crackers very fine.
Mix with nuts and baking powder. Add vanilla to egg whites, beat to stiff foam.
Combine dry mixture and egg mixture; mix well.
Butter 9-inch Pyrex pie plate, spread crust in and up sides.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool, put in refrigerator.

title: mom's chocolate covered cherries
directions: Blend well.
Mixture should be stiff enough to roll into balls.
Chill well.

title: best bars
directions: Put in layers in order in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spiced cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Combine salt, garlic, pickling spice, lemon juice and water in a medium saucepan.
Add cauliflower and cook, uncovered, 5 minutes, until barely crisp-tender.
Chill.
Combine mayonnaise and pickle.
Place drained cauliflower on lettuce leaves and top with dressing. Serves 4.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Spread refried beans in glass baking pan.
In mixing bowl, mix sour cream and taco mix.
Spread mixture on top of beans.
Add green chili peppers on top of sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Serve with corn chips.

title: baked eggs
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until mixture is set and top is golden, about 45 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: fruit yum yum
directions: Melt butter and mix with crumbs.
In separate bowl, mix Dream Whip and milk.
Add sugar and cream cheese.
Beat until thick.
In a flat serving dish or pan, spread all but 1/4 cup crumb mixture. Spread half of cream mixture over crumbs.
Pour pie filling over it, then spread other half of cream mix over pie filling. Sprinkle crumbs on top.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat it in a bowl, pumpkin.

title: gingerbread
directions: Combine egg, sugar, molasses, butter and water; mix well.
In large bowl, stir together the flour, baking soda, ginger and salt. Add molasses mixture.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: sour milk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Cut in shortening. Add buttermilk until blended.
Roll 3/8-inch thick.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes in 475° oven.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Use 9x13 pyrex dish.
Layer chicken, celery, and onion rings. Spread soup and chicken broth over top.
Spread pimiento, onions, chow mein noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.
Add chopped cashews last 10 minutes.

title: party cakes
directions: Mix 2 eggs, butter and cake mix.
Spread in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add 2 eggs, vanilla and 3 cups powdered sugar.
Spread over batter mix. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: fried oysters
directions: Drain oysters.
Pour 1 cup cold water over oysters.
Dry oysters between towels.
Beat egg and 2 tablespoons of water together.
Dip oysters in egg, inserting fork into tough muscle of oysters.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Dip in egg and crumbs again.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Fry in deep fat heated to 375° for 4 minutes or saute in butter.
Makes 2 servings.

title: german green cabbage salad
directions: Shred or chop the cabbage. Dice the pepper and green onions, using some of the green onion stems.
Salt and pepper lightly. Mix in a jar or blender the remaining ingredients.
Pour over cabbage. Cover well and refrigerate overnight.
Pour off some of the dressing before serving, if necessary.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs after beating.
Add mashed bananas.
Add flour with soda added.
Beat well, then stir in nuts.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until straw comes out clean.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with meat mallet. Spread Dijon mustard on one side of each chicken breast. Sprinkle shredded Monterey Jack cheese over mustard and roll chicken breast so mustard and cheese sides are on inside. Secure with toothpick. Coat bottom of skillet with olive oil.
Heat 2 pats of oleo or 1 teaspoon in skillet. Add rolled chicken breasts to heated skillet.

Lightly brown chicken, then add vermouth and green onions. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat until chicken is done (10 to 20 minutes depending on thickness of chicken breasts). Continue adding more vermouth as liquid evaporates.

title: broccoli and noodles supreme
directions: Cook noodles; add broccoli to noodles about the last 10 minutes of cooking time and drain.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: frozen fruit salad
