directions: Soften cream cheese; blend in mayonnaise and add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Add fruits that have been drained well and chilled.
Freeze.
Thaw approximately 30 minutes before serving.

title: chinese chewies
directions: Spray oblong baking dish with Bakers Joy. Mix all ingredients and pour into pan. Bake at 350 for 35 minutes. Let cool and cut into squares and sift powered sugar on top, if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery, onions and mushrooms until tender.
Add the soups, chicken and spaghetti.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan; add cheese to top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs well together.
Add dry ingredients to butter and sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk and beaten eggs.
Add blackberry jam, nuts and vanilla.
Grease and lightly flour four 9-inch cake pans.
Pour in cake batter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back from light pressure of finger.

title: cajun gumbo
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and Creole seasoning and then brown with the sausage; pour off fat and put aside.

title: harriet's caramel nut pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and shortening.
Add the brown and white sugars.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating until creamy.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; add alternately with the milk and vanilla until well blended.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: creamed corn
directions: Stir flour into melted butter in mixing bowl.
Stir in corn and whipping cream.
Pour mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir and bake 15 minutes more.

title: smothered hamburger steak patties
directions: Mix hamburger, Lipton onion soup mix, egg, 1 tablespoon of cream of chicken soup and crackers until patty mixture.
Make patties, they will be real soft.
Pat in flour.
Fry in hot oil until brown.
Heat cream of soups and water together and put 1/2 of mixture in bottom of baking pan.
Add patties.
Pour rest of soup mixture over patties.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until patties are done.

title: apple cinnamon cake
directions: Mix
cake mix as directed.
Peel, core and slice apples. Take the 2
cups
of
apples,
pour over 1 cup of sugar and add cinnamon.
Stir well until sugar and cinnamon coats the apples. First, pour
in well greased pan the apples, pour cake mix over top and bake at 375° until cake is done.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Combine water and butter in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until butter is melted.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add sugar, mixing well.
Beat with spoon until frosting reaches spreading consistency.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skin.
When done, cool, peel and slice thin. Combine bouillon, oil, vinegar, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir into potatoes gently.
Liquid will be absorbed.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour, measure baking powder and salt.
Mix eggs and milk, then shortening.
Mix only until smooth.
Bake in hot waffle iron 3 to 5 minutes or until done.
Serve hot with butter and syrup.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: (May line graham cracker box with waxed paper; cake should fit in it after preparation!)

title: mexican party dip
directions: First Layer:
Smooth bean dip out and cup edges.

title: joan's strawberry bread
directions: Mix in a large bowl the flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and sugar. Mix in another bowl the remaining ingredients. Mix together. Grease and flour pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 1 Bundt cake and one loaf or 3 loaves. Great served with Cool Whip.

title: manicotti casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain grease off.
Mix cheeses and meat together.
Stuff the cooked shells with mixture.
Cover cake pan with spaghetti sauce and put shells on top.
Cover with more sauce.
Cover pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Pound chicken breasts between 2 pieces of plastic wrap until very thin.
Set aside in refrigerator.
To make filling, thaw spinach; squeeze dry and chop bacon and garlic.
Fry bacon; pour off most all fat.
Add spinach and garlic; saute 2 to 3 minutes. Cool until it can be handled.
To assemble, place 1/4 of filling mix in center of each chicken breast.
Roll up and tuck ends under.
Roll in the bread crumbs to which you have added the cheese and oregano.
Put in a baking dish and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve over pasta or rice.
Can be served plain or with a mild tomato sauce or a light cream sauce.

title: cream cheese custard
directions: Put everything in your Osterizer or blender and mix.
Spray mold with cooking spray.
Add a light coating of pancake syrup, spreading it all over the mold.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until done.
Eat with vanilla ice cream and whipped cream.

title: 50% whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
In another bowl, combine sugar, salt, shortening, milk and boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm; add yeast plus 2 1/2 cups unbleached flour (unsifted). Slowly add 3 cups stone whole wheat flour (unsifted).

title: gooseberry pie
directions: Put crumbs on bottom of unbaked crust.
Combine gooseberries, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Fill crust; top with strips or vented top crust, sealing well by moistening edges with water.
Trim and flute edges.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until crust is brown and juices nicely thickened.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 8 x 13-inch pan and spread bottom of pan with pecans and coconut.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over top of cake.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits.
Wrap and then seal around apples.
Bring other ingredients to a boil and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° 30 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all the above ingredients and shape into small balls; cook until browned or place on a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: cherry coffeecake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Slowly add the sugar.
Add the baking powder to the flour.
Add alternately with the oil.
Beat on low.
Add vanilla and salt.
Put all but 1 cup in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spoon on pie filling.
Spoon rest of dough on top.

title: vegetable medley
directions: On 15-inch round glass dish, place head of cauliflower in center.
Arrange broccoli and carrots around outside.
Pour butter over veggies.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
Cover with plastic wrap, turning back one edge to vent.
Microwave at High for 17 to 19 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix meal and onions; add buttermilk and sweet milk.
Add eggs; add water to get right consistency.
Drop by tablespoon into hot fish grease.
Turn until brown.

title: chicken in a pan
directions: Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir well Russian dressing, preserves, onion soup mix and water.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Open and add pineapple and pepper strips.
Bake 1/2 hour long and spoon mixture over chicken.

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add rice, salt and pepper to taste.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg whites, together.
Beat egg whites and fold into cake mixture.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: mothers rolled sugar cookies
directions: Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: wesson oil chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: amish yum-a-setta
directions: Combine beef, onion and sugar.
In deep casserole dish, layer meat mixture, soup, noodles and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese chicken noodle soup
directions: Heat chicken and enough water to cover chicken.
Cover and simmer about 40 minutes.
Cool chicken and broth quickly.
Remove chicken from broth, skin and bone.
Cut into bite-size pieces. Skim fat from broth.
Place chicken pieces in broth with remaining ingredients except vermicelli.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat. Simmer uncovered until carrots are crisp and tender (about 20 minutes).
Remove ginger root.
Stir in vermicelli.
Simmer uncovered until tender, about 5 minutes.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Roll out dough on cookie sheet.
Spread applesauce on dough, then dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Put top crust on and bake.
Ice as soon as it is taken from oven.

title: miniature quiche
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix and put in 2 graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In 6-quart saucepot, heat oil over medium-high heat and brown chicken pieces. Add mushrooms and cook

2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in crushed tomatoes, soup mix, wine and basil. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 30 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Serve, if desired, over hot cooked noodles or rice. Yield: 4 servings.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets.
Cool and peel.
Shred potatoes. Heat cheese and 4 tablespoons margarine until cheese is almost melted.
Remove from heat and add sour cream, onions, salt and pepper; blend well.
Fold in potatoes and spoon into a 2-quart buttered casserole.
Dot with remaining 2 tablespoons margarine and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk.
Heat and add cheese; stir until melted. Add chicken.
Cook noodles and put in a 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add soup mixture and stir.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until mixture bubbles.

title: snowball pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, margarine, nuts and pineapple together.
In a round dish, make a layer of vanilla wafers (place 3 on top of each other).
Spread mixture on wafers.
Top with whipped cream and garnish with coconut.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and shortening.
Add 1 egg yolk at a time, beating after each.
Mix together soda and buttermilk and add alternately with flour to first mixture.
Stir in nuts, coconut, pineapple and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Grease 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice with 1/2 stick margarine.
Saute onion with 1/2 stick margarine until clear.
Add can of soup and 1/2 can milk. Add small Cheez Whiz.
Keep on low heat.
Cook broccoli spears in salted water and drain.
Chop.
Spread layer of rice in casserole dish.
Spread some of cheese sauce, then broccoli alternately layering until all used.
Top with Ritz crackers.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Then add all ingredients together.
Add enough olive juice and mayonnaise to spreading consistency wanted.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and egg yolks together; slowly add 1 cup of the milk.
Beat with a mixer until smooth.
Put the other 2 cups milk in a pan and bring to a boil.
Slowly add sugar mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until boiling and thick.
Add coconut; cool and pour into baked and cooled pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar with 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Beat until sugar is dissolved and whites are stiff. Pile onto pie; seal edges good.
Sprinkle coconut on top of meringue.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add other ingredients and fold in until well mixed.
Place in buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: cheese spread
directions: Chop onion fine.
Mix all ingredients together until smooth and let set overnight.
Makes a large quantity.
Especially good on club crackers.

title: sweet milk hush puppies
directions: Mix to stiff batter using sweet milk; drop with spoon into hot, deep fat and fry until golden brown.

title: chilly cucumber soup
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Cut 12 paper thin slices; reserve.
Chop remaining cucumbers into 1/2-inch pieces.
In medium saucepan, saute onions in butter or oleo until soft.
Add cucumbers, garlic, broth, salt, vinegar, dill and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into food processor and puree until smooth.
Allow soup to cool for 10 minutes.
Stir in yogurt.
Chill well.
Garnish with reserved cucumber and dill weed or mint.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into mixed flour and salt. Place egg in a 1 cup measuring cup. Add vinegar, finish filling cup with ice water. Mix good, then add to flour mixture. Place on floured surface and roll out.

title: see's candy
directions: Cook sugar, oleo and milk to full rolling boil for 6 minutes. Stir constantly.
Remove from fire.
Add marshmallow cream, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour in large flat pan.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Boil 1 cup water.
Beat egg.
Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add shortening and sugar.
Put in 1 cup boiling water; let cool. Mix all together and add flour.

title: diabetic raisin pie
directions: Put raisins in boiling water.
Drain.
Set aside.
Warm on low heat milk.
Add cornstarch that has been mixed with a little water.
Beat up an egg yolk in this mixture.
Pour slowly into milk; add vanilla, salt, butter and sweetener.
Cook on low heat until thick and bubbly.
Add raisins and pour into a cooled pie shell.
Top with your favorite meringue.

title: cream cheese candy
directions: Melt cream cheese; add sugar and pecans.
Mix well and drop on foil and refrigerate.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease 9 x 12 inch pan.
Melt butter in milk.
Remove from stove and stir in other ingredients and mix well.
Pour over one loaf of torn up bread.
Tear up other loaf and put on top of pudding.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place crackers or corn flakes, crumbled on top.
Melt or slice margarine and put on top of crackers or corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crisp pea salad
directions: Put in layers in a bowl.
For first layer, use part of lettuce, onions, celery and chestnuts.
For second layer, sprinkle with peas, salt, celery, onions and cheese.
For third layer, use lettuce.
For fourth layer, seal top with mayonnaise; sprinkle with cheese.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop peppers and tomatoes.
Add cheese and kidney beans.
When ready to serve, add corn chips and dressing.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fill greased muffin tins half full.
Let rise 15 minutes or cook immediately at 450°, 15 minutes or until brown.
Tastes like sour dough biscuits.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Stir in chips and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add celery salt.
Brown ground meat.
Add to sauce. Simmer 5 minutes.

title: kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into cake mix.
Mix in coconut. Pat mixture lightly into an ungreased oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch), building up edges slightly.
Bake for 10 minutes. Arrange peach slices on top of mixture.

title: sugar pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar slightly with fork.
Beat in eggs.
Add lemon
juice and flour.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until brown and filling is set.

title: cherry-cola dessert
directions: Drain cherries, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup and bring to a boil.
Dissolve jello in measure liquid.
Add cola and chill until slightly thickened.
Add cherries and pour into individual dessert dishes.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours. Garnish with whipped topping, if desired.

title: humdinger cookies
directions: Melt butter and sugar in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add dates.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in cereal, pecans and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Divide into 2 portions.
Shape each into a log.
Roll in confectioners sugar; wrap in waxed paper.
Chill for several hours.
Slice into 1-inch pieces.

title: chicken balls
directions: Shape into balls and roll in chopped coconut or chopped nuts.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown finely chopped onion and sausage in little oil.
Drain cooked noodles and rinse in cold water.
Mix all ingredients together and put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs or crushed Club crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 6-layer casserole
directions: Layer first five ingredients in order.
Season the layers, if desired.
Mix together mushrooms and brown sugar.
Put over top of last layer. Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: "backyard deer barbecue"
directions: Wash and trim hindquarter.
Place in the middle of a large piece of heavy-duty foil.
(You need enough foil to make a "packet" around hindquarter, leaving about 2-inches between top of hindquarter and foil.)
Take a knife and make 4 to 6 slits in top of meat to allow juices to flow through.
Rub salt and pepper over it.
Place whole slice of country ham on top, covering as much of the hindquarter as possible.
Place uncooked bacon slices lengthwise on top of ham.
Seal up foil packet; place on grill (or in oven) on low for 4 to 6 hours until done.
(Check every 30 to 45 minutes to keep from drying out.)
Remove cooked hindquarter, ham and bacon from foil; chop them all up together, including juices. Stir in barbecue sauce and salsa.
(You may need to add more or less barbecue sauce and salsa depending on size of hindquarter.) Serve warm on buns and enjoy!
Delicious!

title: carol's candy
directions: Mix sugar, cream and margarine in 4-quart heavy saucepan.
Mix well and put on stove; start to boil.
Cook on medium for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Take off stove and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir for 5 minutes.
Pour into pan greased with margarine.

title: orange kiss me cake
directions: Thaw 6 ounces frozen orange juice concentrate.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except nuts and raisins.
Blend, then beat 3 minutes.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Drizzle remaining orange concentrate on warm cake.
Sprinkle topping over cake.

title: green beans with walnuts and walnut oil
directions: Cook beans in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Rinse beans with cold water and drain well.
(Can be prepared ahead of time.) Melt butter with oil in heavy large skillet over high heat.
Add beans and toss until heated through, about 4 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper. Add walnuts and parsley and toss.
Transfer to bowl and serve.

title: creamy mushroom soup
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter with olive oil. Add shallots and cook until tender, 2 to 3 minutes. Add sliced mushrooms, thyme, salt and pepper, cooking until all of the liquid rendered from mushrooms evaporates. Remove 1/2 cup mushrooms and reserve. Stir in flour and cook 2 to 3 minutes. Add 3 cups of chicken broth; bring to simmer and cook for 15 minutes. In a blender, puree soup in batches until smooth. Return to saucepan; bring to simmer and whisk in milk. Add reserved chicken broth to achieve desired consistency. Adjust seasoning with salt, pepper and nutmeg. Lower heat and whisk in 1/4 cup of sour cream. Keep soup hot; do not simmer or boil. Serve with remaining sour cream and reserved mushrooms.

title: berry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil a 9-inch pie pan or spray with a nonstick cooking spray.
Place berries in a large bowl. Sprinkle with sugar and cornstarch.
Toss to coat berries.
Place in prepared pan.

title: chicken pie and biscuits
directions: Cook the chicken in water until done.
Pick chicken off bones and put in baking dish.
Mix in a jar the cold water and flour; shake and add to the boiling chicken broth until thickened.
Cover chicken with gravy.
Make biscuits and put on top of chicken and gravy mixture.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tropical fruit vinaigrette
directions: Place papaya, mango, kiwi, pineapple and vinegar in heavy saucepan.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes over medium heat.
Cool mixture in refrigerator for approximately 30 minutes.

title: corn on the cobb with savory lime butter
directions: Remove husks from fresh ears of corn. Scrub with a stiff brush to remove silks. Rinse and cook uncovered in enough lightly salted boiling water to cover ears. Cook for 5 - 7 minutes or until tender. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, thoroughly combine the butter, savory and lime peel. Serve herb butter with hot corn. Store any remaining butter, covered in the refrigerator.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into pieces. Cook all vegetables separately until slightly tender; drain well. Slice mushrooms; saut mushrooms and onions in butter for 10 minutes. Combine soup, milk and cheese. Heat until cheese melts. Add mushroom-onion mixture to soup mixture. Layer vegetables in a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Pour soup mixture over vegetables. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: pineapple sparkle punch
directions: Combine the juices and the sugar; chill.
Add club soda and ginger ale just before serving.

title: merry dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender on medium speed; blend until creamy smooth.
Chill and serve with fruit.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Combine and thoroughly mix shortening, sugar and eggs. Combine and sift flour, cream of tartar and salt.
Stir into shortening mixture; add vanilla.
Roll into balls.
Make mixture of sugar and cinnamon and roll balls in it.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: turkey pita
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stuff pitas.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cube 2 slices bread.
Place in a greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Combine chicken, onion, celery, mayonnaise, salt and pepper in bowl.
Spoon over bread.
Top with remaining bread slices. Beat eggs and milk and pour over bread and chicken.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours.
Spoon soup over bread and sprinkle with cheese and cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand covered 5 minutes before serving.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and powdered sugar.
Blend in flour.
Press evenly in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread over hot baked layer.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Cool and cut into 3 1/2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 32.
While warm, spread with Orange Lemon Icing.

title: polish dill pickles
directions: Wash pickles, quarter and pack in jars, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Wash and add garlic, dill, grape leaf and hot pepper; mix together.
Bring vinegar, water and canning salt to a boil and pour over pickles; seal.
Place jars in hot water to cover jars. Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Take out of cooker.

title: turkey potato casserole
directions: Put butter, mushrooms and onion into a 2-quart casserole. Cook, uncovered, about 4 minutes at High or until mushrooms are tender.
Stir after 1 minute.
Then put turkey, potatoes, parsley, seasoned salt and pepper into casserole.
Add evaporated milk gradually, stirring gently.
Heat mixture, uncovered, about 5 minutes on High; stir once during heating.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ham bake
directions: Prepare
dinner as directed;
add ham and green pepper. Season to
taste.
Place in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Combine milk and eggs;
pour over dinner mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: microwave brunswick stew
directions: Place chicken, tomatoes, 1 cup water, onion and bay leaves in large casserole.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover; microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave on Medium for 15 minutes. Stir in carrots, celery and peas.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaves; stir in cornstarch mixture. Microwave on High for 5 to 10 minutes, until chicken is done and mixture thickens.

title: vinegar cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Then add liquids, mix with fork.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: homemade banana layer cake
directions: Grease and flour two round cake pans.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix on low speed until combined, then 3 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tests done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes on wire rack.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Use any frosting or in banana split cake.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Combine the first 10 ingredients in a saucepan and simmer for several minutes or until well blended. Let stand until cool. Rinse the chicken wings, drain well and pat dry. Place the wings in a large container and add the marinade, mixing to coat well. Marinate the wings in the refrigerator for 3 hours or longer. Drain the wings, reserving the marinade. Arrange the wings in a single layer in foil-lined baking pans. Brush generously with the reserved marinade. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Brush with reserved marinade. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes longer or until the wings are crispy. Arrange the wings on serving platter. Yield: 200 chicken wings.

title: steak and onion pie
directions: Combine 3 tablespoons flour, 1 teaspoon salt, paprika, pepper, ginger and allspice; coat beef cubes with flour mixture.
Cook beef cubes in hot oil, stirring frequently.
When beef begins to change color, add onion and saute until well browned.
Add beef broth; cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour. Add potatoes and cook 20 minutes.
Combine 2 tablespoons flour and water; gradually stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain and place in casserole. Add cheese on top of broccoli.
Pour 1/3 of the margarine on top of broccoli and cheese.
Sprinkle crackers on top, then pour rest of margarine over crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Wash beans, cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Place in 5 to 6-quart pot.
Add water to 1 1/2 inches above beans.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to boil; adjust burner to simmer.
Add baking soda.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Remove 1 cup beans, drained.
Mash and return to pot.

title: corn bread
directions: Grease a number 5 iron skillet.
Mix meal, flour, milk and water.
Bake at 450° to 500° until brown.

title: janet's relish
directions: Chop the vegetables medium with meat grinder blade.
Add pickling salt; let stand overnight.
Wash and drain well.
Boil the sugar, water, cider vinegar, celery seed, turmeric and mustard seed.
Add vegetables; bring just to a boil.
Seal in canning jars.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and spoon into well-greased muffin tins. Do not use paper liners.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour evenly over muffins. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until browned.

title: flounder florentine
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Place in greased shallow casserole. Sprinkle with onion, seasonings and oil.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Blend in milk; stir until thickened.
Season with additional salt.
Add vermouth.
If using frozen fish, thaw and squeeze out water between paper towels. Place fillets over spinach.
Pour white sauce over all; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blueberry or blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cut in butter or margarine.
Add milk and beat until smooth.
Cover bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan with fruit.
Pour batter over fruit.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cornstarch and sprinkle evenly over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix the dry ingredients; add egg yolk and mix well.
Add vinegar and oil gradually, beating constantly with an eggbeater until mixture thickens.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Set aside. Cream egg, sugar and butter.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Stir in bananas (walnuts may be added here).
Bake in slow 325° oven for about 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: louisiana fig cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla in bowl; beat with spoon and add oil and beat again.
Sift and add all dry ingredients.
Mix well; add mashed figs to batter and mix well.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and other ingredients; place in baked pie shell.
Top with mashed potatoes, cheese and bacon bits.
Place in oven until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: impossible chili cheese pie
directions: I add browned sausage to this; top with sour cream and picante sauce.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs.
Add potatoes, vanilla extract and melted butter.
Mix, then add milk.
Cook in unbaked pie shell for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet and sour broccoli(yields 4 servings)
directions: In a large skillet or wok, heat 2 tablespoons oil, then add garlic.
Saute 30 seconds.
Add broccoli and water.
Cover and cook 2 minutes.
Uncover.
Add 1 teaspoon oil and saute or stir-fry about 30 seconds.
Mix sugar with the vinegar and add to pot, tossing thoroughly with broccoli.
Season to taste.
Enjoy!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla, then add zucchini.
Combine the flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon; add to egg mixture.
Put into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: apricot pork cutlets
directions: Saute cutlets in hot margarine, two minutes each side;
do not overcook.
Just before done, spoon 1 teaspoon
preserves over each cutlet.
Let melt and run down into pan.
Remove cutlets to hot plate and keep warm.
Add apricot brandy and dried apricots to pan drippings.
Stir and reduce heat.
Pour sauce over cutlets and serve.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion in margarine.
Combine soups, chilies, broth and jalapenos and add to onion.
Pour 1/3 of the sauce into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer 1/2 the quartered tortillas, 1/2 the chicken, another 1/3 sauce and 1/2 the cheese.
Repeat layers and top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve 6.

title: baked seasoned salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Arrange a single layer of fish in a shallow baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour half of the sauce mixture over the fish. Bake for 20 minutes, basting with the remaining sauce. Sprinkle with paprika and chopped parsley. Serves 4.

title: apple cider pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine next 4 ingredients. Add to creamed mixture alternately with apple cider, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Mix just until blended after each addition. Stir in vanilla. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan. Cool completely.

title: brownie candy cups
directions: Add enough liquid to cake mix to consistency of waffle batter, then bake in waffle iron.
Can be eaten warm or cold, with jam or glaze icing.

title: crab and rice
directions: Open and clean crabs.
Rinse off excess seasoning to remove salt.
Place all vegetables and seasonings in a frying pan with the butter.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste; allow to penetrate seasoning for about 5 minutes.
Add crabs and water. Cook for 25 minutes.
Add rice.
Cook on top of stove or bake in oven (350°) until rice is tender.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In pot, place cranberries, sugar and water.
Cook until berries are soft.
Let cool slightly.
Add Jell-O, then add celery and nuts.
Place in dessert dish and chill.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix as directed on box; let cool.
In a punch bowl, crumble 1/3 of cake.
Pour 1 1/2 cups strawberries and juice over cake.
Layer 1/2 of pudding over strawberries.
Sprinkle 1/2 of coconut, then sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans.
Repeat all layers once more; top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with coconut and pecans.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and remove meat from bones.
In large casserole dish, layer chicken and Doritos.
Mix soup, tomatoes and broth together and pour over chicken and Doritos. Top with lots of grated Cheddar cheese and bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until mixed well.
Cover and chill. Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: new year's bean soup
directions: Wash the beans/peas thoroughly.
Place in a large kettle. Cover with water and add the salt.
Soak overnight.
In the morning, rinse again.
Drain and add the water and ham or ham bones.
Bring to a boil and simmer at least 3 hours.
Add the onion, tomatoes, chili powder, garlic, bay leaf, juice of lemon and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 2 more hours and enjoy. Freezes well.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Bring water, onion, base and broccoli to boil.
Mix gravy with enough of the milk to mix according to the package.
Add gravy mix to water mixture.
Add gravy until desired thickness is achieved. Add cheese to mixture and stir.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Melt cheese over top and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread on party ryes and then bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: blanche's foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt. Cut shortening into mixture with knife or pastry tool until crumbly.
Stir in milk and vinegar just until mixed.
Add flour to roll out.
Handle as little as possible. Bake according to recipe or for pie shell at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes a two crust pie.
Almost always delicious!

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage until done; drain on paper towels and set aside. Beat eggs in a bowl.
Add milk, salt and mustard.
In bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, arrange bread cubes in layer. Top with sausage, sprinkle on cheese.
Pour on egg mixture over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil after half way cooked.

title: sausage balls
directions: With hands, combine sausage and cheese and then add Bisquick. Shape into balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: meatball sandwiches
directions: In a large bowl, combine meat, egg, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch meatballs.
In a large skillet, thoroughly brown meatballs on all sides in vegetable oil; drain fat.
Add sauce; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Fill rolls with sliced meatballs.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes to melt cheese.

title: pan-fried chicken
directions: Mix egg and milk together.
Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture, then shake chicken in a paper bag containing flour, salt, paprika and pepper, until evenly coated.
Spread on rack to dry coating.

title: cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 2 sheet pans.
Beat egg with water.
Lay thawed puff pastry on clean surface and brush each piece with egg wash.
Sprinkle cheese over egg mixture and pat down.
